title: colorful fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss gently.
Cover and chill. Serves 8.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cover.
Let stand overnight. Rinse and drain.
In a large pot, place zucchini-onion mixture and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Pack hot relish into sterile pint jars and process in hot water bath for 20 minutes or use the directions with your processor.

title: shredded potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Let potatoes cool, then peel. Shred with salad shooter.
Spray bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Cover with layer of potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Pour on 1/2 of whipping cream. Put another layer of potatoes, seasonings and butter.
Pour remaining whipping cream over.
Let set 1 hour before baking. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 40 minutes.

title: potato burritos
directions: Brown pork pieces. Add rest of ingredients. Cook down until thickened and fill tortillas for burritos.

title: butterscotch fantastic
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix and press in oblong baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine powdered sugar and cream cheese; beat until fluffy.
Fold 2 cups whipped topping in.
Spread over crust.
Combine pudding mix and milk; beat 2 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer.
Chill.

title: sandy's sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator and use as needed. Roll dough on floured board and cut biscuits.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: cheese vegetable broil
directions: Break apart cauliflower into small pieces.
Wash under cold water.
Skin, wash and slice carrots into 1/4-inch discs.
Place vegetables in a steamer with cauliflower on the bottom.
Steam until tender, but still have a crunch.
Place in an ovenproof dish. Drizzle with olive oil.
Sprinkle with basil and toss.
Top with Cheddar cheese and place under the broiler until cheese melts. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Sift together 2 cups flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture and mix until blended.
Dredge blueberries in remaining cup of flour; fold gently into batter.
Pour into a 10-inch Bundt pan that has been buttered and coated with sugar.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tests done.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown the hamburger with the onion. Add the garlic salt, salt and pepper. Drain. Add sauces and oregano. In kettle, cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Then mix in soup. Layer in casserole 1/2 the noodles, 1/2 the meat, remaining noodles and rest of the meat. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove cover; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: hungarian beef pot(serves 4)
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown meat. Stir in onion.
Cook until soft.
Stir in beef broth, tomato paste, mustard and garlic powder. Simmer, covered 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and paprika.
Heat slowly to prevent sour cream from curdling.
Do not allow mixture to boil. Serve beef mixture over hot cooked noodles.

title: percolator punch
directions: Mix the first four items in 30-cup percolator.
Place the remaining items in basket of percolator.
Perk for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, yogurt, salt and pepper together in a large mixing bowl. Add the remaining ingredients and toss till thoroughly combined. Chill until ready to serve.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add fruit filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apricot delight salad
directions: Mix jello in hot water; add cold water and then add remaining ingredients and let gel.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread, cheese and sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt and pepper. Pour mixture over bread, cheese and sausage. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. May be refrigerated.

title: death by chocolate dessert
directions: Break brownies apart into small pieces.
Layer brownie pieces, mousse, Cool Whip and Heath bars in clear bowl.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: garden-style barbecue beans
directions: Combine onion and green pepper in 1-quart casserole dish. Microwave on High 2 minutes or until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute onions and stems in butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Fill cups of mushrooms with the mixture and top them with melted butter.
Place in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix together and keep in an air tight jar. Use 2 tsp. to a cup of hot water.

title: hot tuna & cheddar sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix together rice, milk and soups.
Pour mixture into buttered pan or casserole.
Lay chicken breasts on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges; add pineapple, juice and all.
Stir in the lemon pudding (dry).
Chill 2 hours or more.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: rolled chicken
directions: Cook mushrooms in butter about 5 minutes.
Blend in flour; stir in cream and add salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until mixture becomes thick.
Stir in cheese.
Cook over
very low heat, stirring constantly.
Turn mixture into pie plate.
Chill, covered, about 1 hour.
Cut the firm cheese mixture into 6 or 7 portions; shape into sticks.
Make cutlets out of chicken breast by pounding on until it can be rolled.
Place a cheese stick on each chicken breast; roll as a jelly roll; tuck in ends.
Dust with flour; dip in beaten eggs and roll in breadcrumbs.
Chill. Fry in hot oil 5 minutes, then bake in 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In large
skillet, brown meat, which has been rolled in flour, pepper
and
salt,	in
oleo.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic and brown lightly.
Stir in beef broth.
Cover and cook until meat
is tender,
stirring now and then.
After meat is tender, stir in sour
cream
and
cook
over
low
heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over 3 cups cooked noodles.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into 1/4-inch strips.
Brown in hot shortening.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is crisp-tender.
Combine remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Add to meat.
Heat through; do not let boil.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: jam-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift together and add alternately, dry ingredients with milk.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, spread 1/2 the batter in pan.
Cover with preserves; top with more batter.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: graham cookies
directions: Cook for 2 minutes on pan on stove.
Layer cookie sheet with graham crackers broken up, but touching each other.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Break apart.

title: blow your mind pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes; cool.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.

title: colochi
directions: Saute bacon, onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat for approximately 1 hour.
(I suggest that corn not be added until mixture is almost ready to serve as it becomes tough, if cooked the entire time.
Also, garlic salt may be substituted for the garlic clove and salt.)
Serves 4.

title: tart on ember day
directions: Steam the onions 10 to 11 minutes on High in the microwave. Combine with the sage, parsley and cheese; mix well.
Stir in eggs.
Cut up the butter into the mixture and add the sugar, cinnamon, ginger and currants.
Pour into the pie shell.

title: birds
directions: Roll crescent triangles flat.
Place 1 tablespoon of chicken in the middle of each crescent triangle and fold over and seal edges. Place in oblong baking dish.
Mix soup and milk until smooth and pour over crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crescent are slightly brown.

title: oreo delight
directions: Mix together milk, Cool Whip, cream cheese and pudding until smooth.
Next, crush one row of Oreo cookies with a fork into small pieces.
Then put the pieces of cookie in the bottom of a deep dish.
Pour half of the mixture over the bottom row of crushed cookies.
Put another row of crushed cookies in the middle.
Pour the other half of mixture on top.
Then put last row of crushed cookies on top.

title: mom's fried chocolate pies
directions: In small bowl, mix cocoa and sugar to taste.
Mix a pie dough and roll out into turnover.
On turnover, place a slice of margarine, then put 3 teaspoons of cocoa mixture.
Pull over dough and press in edges to make turnover.
Fry in hot pan with cooking oil, until brown on both sides.

title: corn chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle.
Bring to a boil; boil for 15 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars; seal at once.

title: old time irish stew
directions: Brown meat, add onion, garlic, boiling water, and spices. Simmer until meat is tender. Add vegetables and barley. Simmer until done. If using a crock pot: after browning meat put all ingredients into a crock pot and cook on low 7- 8 hours.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions.
Melt cheese together with milk in saucepan.
Put vegetables in casserole dish, pour melted cheese over vegetables.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over top of vegetables.
Cut tabs of margarine and place over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Wash seeds from jack-o-lantern.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Toast at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden.
Sprinkle with salt.
Enjoy!

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel; mash avocados.
Add salt and lemon juice.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, garlic, pepper and onion.
Add Tabasco sauce and onion salt to taste.
Serve with crackers.

title: cole's 7 day pickles
directions: Drain dill pickles in your gallon jar. Place pickles, sugar and cinnamon sticks with pepper and layer until you use all pickles and sugar.
Place lid on jar. Once a day for 7 days, turn jar over. This will mix sugar and pickle chips. On day 7, put pickles in smaller jars; pour juice in jars over chips. Makes 14 (8 ounce) jars.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat butter and milk until butter melts.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cracker snack
directions: Stir until well blended.
You may cut recipe in half.

title: chocolate crinkle top cookies
directions: Beat granulated sugar, butter and vanilla in a large mixer bowl until crumbly.
Beat in melted chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in remaining morsels.
Cover and chill just until firm.
Shape dough in 1 1/2-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool for 2 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove all the seeds and membrane.
Cook peppers in boiling, salted water (1/2 tsp. salt to 1 cup water) 5 minutes. Drain.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10 inch skillet until beef is brown and onion is tender, drain off fat.
Stir in salt, garlic salt, rice and 1 cup of tomato sauce.
Heat until rice is hot.
Stuff each pepper lightly with about 1/2 cup of beef mixture.
Stand peppers upright in baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2 inch. Pour on remaining tomato sauce.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes.
6 servings.

title: grandma's sugar cakes
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until light colored, then add shortening and 1/2 cup of the buttermilk. Place 1 teaspoon of baking soda in the other 1/2 cup of buttermilk.
It will foam, then add to mixture and beat again. Add vanilla and 2 cups of flour and baking powder. Beat again.
Add other flour, mixing well.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Stir together the flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt and add gradually to butter mixture.
Stir in M&M's. Shape dough into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove to cooling racks.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Stir into dry pudding mix.
Add Cool Whip, nuts, coconut and marshmallows.
Mix well; chill.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: In a large saucepan, melt chocolate chips over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add cream cheese and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in pecans and cookie crumbs.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cover and refrigerate until firm (about 2 hours).
Roll in powdered sugar again.
Store in airtight container in the refrigerator or freezer.
Yields about 6 dozen snowballs.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, with mixer, mash potatoes, when lumps are gone, add cream cheese and butter in small pieces, beat well until completely mixed.
Add sour cream, milk, eggs and onions together then add to potato mixture, beat until fluffy.
Place in a greased 9-inch round casserole, refrigerate several hours, or overnight if not using them immediately.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until slightly brown on top.
Serves 8 - 12.
Great do ahead.

title: chili con carne with beans
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add ground chuck with salt and pepper; brown while stirring.
Add chili con carne with beans, tomatoes and onion.
Cook until done or simmer until ready to eat. Eat with soda crackers.

title: teriyaki chicken kabobs
directions: You will also need 10 to 12 skewers.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and cover.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add remaining ingredients.
Let congeal.
Serves about 15.

title: curried chicken bites
directions: Beat cream cheese and Miracle Whip until light and fluffy. Stir in next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill several hours.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen.

title: the best banana bread
directions: Bake at 350°.
Makes 1 large and 1 small loaf.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Place the chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt the margarine in boiling water. Add the stuffing mix. Spoon the stuffing mixture over the chicken.
Mix the soup and water and pour over the stuffing. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a Dutch oven or large roasting pan, fry bacon until crisp; set aside.
Drain fat from pan.

title: dreamland cake
directions: Mix like shortbread and spread in ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: tortilla con polo
directions: Butter casserole (2 1/2-quart). Mix all ingredients together. Let stand 24 hours in the refrigerator. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Serve with taco sauce. Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook chopped broccoli and onion in water for 20 minutes or until soft.
Make sauce with remaining ingredients; slowly add to mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add a lot of seasoned salt to taste. Simmer until ready to serve.
Do not boil!

title: french onion soup(microwave)
directions: Place onions and butter in a large casserole dish. Cook on power 9 for 7 to 8 minutes, until onions are tender. Add beef broth, water and Worcestershire sauce. Cook on power 9, covered, for 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes, until mixture boils. Place toasted French bread on a paper towel; sprinkle on Parmesan cheese and top with Mozzarella slice. Heat on power 9 for 1 minute, just enough to soften cheese. Put a slice of toast in each serving dish and pour hot soup over toast. Quite tasty.

title: sundae sauce
directions: Combine pudding, sugar and water in a saucepan, blending well. Place over low heat and cook until all the sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking until the mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat and mix in the butter.
Serve immediately over ice cream.

title: marinating sauce
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and mix well.
To use on meat or chicken,
marinate	for 3 to 4 hours.
Marinate fish for 2 hours. Cook
on
barbecue grill or under boiler, basting with leftover sauce frequently.

title: brandied fruit melange
directions: In small saucepan, combine brandy, brown sugar and cinnamon stick; mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
In large bowl combine peaches, apples and oranges; mix well.
Pour hot brandy mixture over fruit, mix gently.
Cover, store in refrigerator 8 to 10 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally. Just before serving, remove cinnamon stick.
Add strawberries and kiwi fruit, toss lightly.
Spoon into a bowl.
Yields 16 servings (1/2 cup).

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: italian stew with polenta
directions: Cover bottom of pan with olive oil for frying.
Brown meat, onion, salt and pepper, celery and spices together in frying pan. When browned, put in roasting pan-no need to drain-put in tomato sauce, tomato paste, carrots and garlic.
Stir until well blended together.
Then stir in the wine. Put in 350 degree oven for 2 hours.
Stir frequently-may need to add a little water or wine to taste throughout cooking.

title: rum balls
directions: Grind vanilla wafers and pecans together.
Add cocoa, corn syrup and rum.
Shape into small balls and roll in powdered sugar. Store in refrigerator in a tight container.

title: cheese wreath
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Place drinking glass in center of serving platter.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls of mixture to form ring around glass, just touching outer edge of glass; smooth with spatula.
Remove glass.
Garnish with chopped parsley and pimento just before serving, if desired. Serve with crackers.

title: sweet dough rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and sprinkle in 3 tablespoons sugar.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine milk and rest of sugar, salt and shortening.
Add this mixture to the yeast mixture.
Add the eggs and 1/2 of the flour; stir until smooth. Then add the rest of the flour until it is pliable.

title: mild, fresh tomato salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Can be used after a few hours as is or can be simmered in crock-pot until soft, then cool and use.

title: cheesy ghost on toast
directions: Toast 1 slice of bread.
With butter knife, cut 1 slice of cheese into a ghostly shape.
Use straw to cut out eyes.
Place cheesy ghost on top of toast.
Then enjoy.

title: vanilla almond crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Toast almonds in margarine.
Remove 1/2 of almonds from margarine; set aside.
Combine cereal, brown sugar, coconut and salt with remaining almonds and margarine.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Cool. Spread softened ice cream over top of crust.
Sprinkle with remaining almonds over top of ice cream.
Place in freezer until ready to serve.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add brown sugar and 2 tablespoons of syrup reserved from pineapple.
Add water to remaining syrup to make 1 cup.
Arrange pineapple in bottom of pan.
Place a cherry in each slice of pineapple.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice to mixture.
Put cake mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes; invert on plate when done.

title: "tired of cooking" casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion salt, salt and pepper.
Mix in can of tomato soup.
Gently fold in green beans (juice and all). Pour into casserole dish.
Spread mashed potatoes over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk. Add sufficient flour to work dough.
Roll out and cut.
Bake until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: cocoa swirl coffee cake
directions: Combine
flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl. Cut
in
shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse
crumbs.
Add
eggs,
orange juice and peel; stir
just until blended.
Set batter aside.
Combine powdered sugar, nuts and cocoa in a small bowl.	Stir in melted butter to
form	a crumb
mixture.
Spread
cup reserved batter evenly on bottom
of	a greased 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle half of crumb
mixture over
batter.
Spread
with one cup batter and sprinkle
with remaining crumb mixture.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake
for
to
40 minutes or until cake tester	inserted
in center
comes out clean.
Cool slightly; spread with Orange Glaze. serve warm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ground beef, oatmeal, salt, onions, pepper, egg, and milk; mixing well.
Shape into loaf and place in medium baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes.
Mix catsup, brown sugar, and mustard.
Remove loaf from oven and spread catsup mixture evenly over top and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: currant nut icing
directions: Plump currants by
soaking
in	1/4 cup hot water for 5 minutes. Drain well.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first ingredients.
Add apples. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping on batter and gently press into dough.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Add mincemeat.
Stir; add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by tablespoon.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: candied pecans
directions: Place pecans in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Heat in oven at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: stephanie's baked beans
directions: Drain beans.
Fry 7 to 8 pieces of bacon.
Take bacon out and leave grease.
Saute onion until transparent in grease.
Then add beans, brown sugar, crumbled bacon, ketchup and mustard.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.

title: seafood egg rolls
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok or skillet.
Add celery and mushrooms; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add bean sprouts and green onions; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add shrimp or crab, soy sauce, sesame oil and cornstarch.
Cook, stirring, until sauce thickens.
Cool to room temperature.
Fill each egg roll wrap with 2 tablespoons mixture. Add white pepper to mixture.
Fold in wrap; deep fry a few at a time for about 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: perky punch
directions: Mix the 3 cans of juice together and chill.
When ready to serve, put in punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.

title: veal marsala
directions: Coat veal with a mixture of flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Heat garlic and oil in a large heavy skillet until garlic is slightly browned.
Add meat to oil and garlic in skillet, brown slowly on both sides.

title: homemade orange sherbet
directions: Mix orange drink, crushed pineapple and condensed milk and pour into churn and fill the rest of the way up with regular milk. Churn as usual.
Enjoy!

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Cook meat in water until brown.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook on low 3 hours, stirring often.
Serve over spaghetti with grated Cheddar cheese and chopped onion.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients; put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake according to directions; pour into pan.
Place margarine and cream cheese in a saucepan; heat until warm and melted.
Stir in sugar.
Spoon over the cake batter.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
After cooling, cut into squares to serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well and make loaf.
Place 1 ounce barbecue sauce in bottom of casserole dish.
Add loaf.
Top with 1 ounce more of barbecue sauce.
Bake 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: linguine with triple red sauce
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium high heat.
Add garlic, diced bell pepper and crushed red pepper.
Saute until bell pepper softens about 5 minutes.
Add roasted peppers, linguine, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Toss until coated.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the eggs, vanilla and butter.
Fluff sugars together.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and add to the sugars.
In large (very large) bowl, combine all together.
Fold in 3 large bags of chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not bake until brown, just 10 minutes.
Makes 12 to 13 dozen.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook chicken with 6 to 8 cups of water and salt to taste. Cook onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Mix bread crumbs with seasonings.
Add cooked onion and celery and enough broth from cooked chicken to make a batter about as thick as cornbread batter.
Pour 1/2 batter in buttered baking pan.
Place deboned chicken on top of dressing.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: double crust pizza casserole
directions: Filling:
In a 12-inch skillet, combine the beef, sausage and onion.
Fry until onion is tender and meat is no longer pink. Stir in the tomato sauce, olives, tomato paste, seasoning mix and garlic powder.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Take some morning sunshine, add a smile, some kind words, too. Add a little thoughtfulness, stir just enough to blend.
Serve it warm with loving hands.
It's the making of a friend!

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, gelatin and cornstarch.
Stir in boiling water; let cool.
Arrange strawberries in pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries and refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: the ultimate rice pudding...raisins optional
directions: Rinse rice and cook in 6 cups of milk. Add salt. At low boil, simmer 20 minutes. Add sugar. Simmer until mixture thickens. Blend eggs in 1/2 cup milk. Add egg/milk mixture and vanilla to rice. Bring to a boil. Add cream. Return to boil. Remove from heat. Stir in raisins. Add spice to taste. Cool and refrigerate.

title: rusyn crepes(palachinki)
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together. Add milk and flour. Mix together. Should look like thick cream. Fry spoonfuls and fill with dry cottage cheese mix of remaining ingredients. Fill palachinki/crepes. Roll and place in buttered baking dish. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Serve with sour cream, honey, jelly, syrup.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix ingredients in pan and cook until thick.

title: gelatin cubes
directions: Dissolve flavored and unflavored gelatin in boiling water. Chill until firm.
Cut into cubes.

title: apple cranberry pie
directions: Soak cranberries in 1/4 cup sugar and water.
Peel and cut up apples.
Stew apples in brown sugar and butter until tender.
Add cranberries, stirring until tender.
Pour apples and cranberry mixture with juice into pie crust.
Put other pie crust on top. Trim off excess crust.
Cut vent in center and brush with butter. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: coleslaw
directions: Chop cabbage and onion with salt. Add Miracle Whip and some sugar to taste.

title: chess pie(a southern dish)
directions: In medium bowl, combine brown sugar, eggs, milk, lemon juice and liqueur or flavoring.
Beat well until smooth and well mixed. Add margarine slowly, beating until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into unbaked shell.
To keep edges of crust from burning, put strips of aluminum foil around edges until last few minutes of baking.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool before cutting.
Serve warm or cold, plain or with ice cream (vanilla, pecan, pralines and cream) or whipped cream.

title: ham and cheese muffin
directions: Cook rice according to box directions.
Place approximately 2 ounces of ham and a slice of tomato on toasted muffin.
Put 1/4 cup of rice on tomato and cover with slice of cheese. Heat and melt cheese in toaster-broiler.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle crumbs in bottom of 7-inch spring-form pan.
Position knife blade in food processor.
Process cream cheese and next 6 ingredients until smooth; add egg.
Blend well.
Fold chocolate chips in.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes. Let cool on rack.
Cover and chill for 6 to 8 hours.
Remove sides of pan and transfer to serving platter.

title: applesauce nut cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add cinnamon, cloves, cocoa, walnuts and baking powder.
Then add hot applesauce with dissolved baking soda.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: black cherry jello salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on package.
Boil in saucepan pineapple and sugar for 1 minute.
Add to jello; add pecans.
Let cool in refrigerator.
When almost set, add 1 can Eagle Brand milk; mix and serve.

title: raisin squares
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Put half of this oatmeal mixture in oblong greased pan, pat it down.
Mix sugar and flour well.
Add juice, water, cinnamon and raisins in saucepan.
Cook until thick. Spread a thin amount of raisin mixture between layers of oatmeal mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool, cut in squares.

title: crumb topped brussels sprouts
directions: In a saucepan, cook Brussels sprouts in salted water until crisp and tender, about 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Place in an ungreased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Drizzle with 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese and remaining butter; sprinkle over Brussels sprouts.
Cover and bake at 325° for 10 minutes; uncover and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: homemade croutons
directions: Spread butter on both sides of your slices of bread (preferably not real fresh).
Cut the slices into cubes.
Shake garlic salt, onion and celery salt on them (or any combination of seasonings you prefer).
Put on baking sheet in 250° oven and bake for approximately 1 hour.

title: fried okra
directions: Combine okra, milk, salt and pepper in a shallow dish.
Let stand one hour, or until most of milk is absorbed.
Dredge okra in cornmeal.
Fry okra in hot oil (375°) until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Transfer okra to serving platter.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 250° until warm (can make ahead and freeze).

title: leek soup
directions: Saute leeks, onions and garlic until soft.
Cook potatoes with all ingredients.
When soft, blend in blender.
Add milk until thin.
Heat and serve.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix together crackers, sugar and oleo.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix well 2 eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese. Pour into crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix together in large saucepan:
pumpkin, 3 egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and cloves.
Cook until thick. Add gelatin, dissolved in 1/4 cup cool water, to pumpkin mixture. Beat 3 egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold in pumpkin mixture. Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley flakes, bouillon cube and seasonings; mix well. Cover; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, mixing until blended.
Add milk mixture to vegetables; cook until thickened.
Add process cheese spread; stir until melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and let stand 1 hour.
Add whipped cream and fold gently.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: *Chopped jalapeno peppers can be substituted for green peppers.

title: mustard dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use for dip for pretzels.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let stand in refrigerator until firm or overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas, sour milk and lemon juice.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add to other items.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans.
Bake 60 minutes at 350° in loaf pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze chopped spinach until dry.
Stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Blend well.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Boil water; add dates and soda, set aside.
Sift flour, salt and powder; set aside.
Cream sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs. Gradually alternate adding flour mixture and date mixture, then stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a 13 x 9-inch pan, 2 loaf pans or 5 vegie cans.

title: salsa vinaigrette
directions: Mix tomatoes, onion, jalapeno and lime juice.
Salt to taste. With motor running, add oil in a stream.
Stir coriander in vinaigrette.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and put in a large pan and put ice over them for a few hours.
Then slice thin and pack in jars which have a few slices of onions in bottom.
Then add brine, which has been boiled together.
Fill each jar up to the neck and add a head of dill on top.
Seal and cold pack until pickles turn color.

title: spadini
directions: Pound beef until thin.
Put some onion in the middle of one. Add 1 teaspoon parsley, cheese and black pepper.
Now tuck in the ends and roll the meat into a cylinder shape.
Try not to let stuffing fall out.
Now roll the spadini in the egg wash and then into the frying pan on medium heat.
Turn until all sides are brown, then cover them to make sure the stuffing is done.
Bon appetit.

title: skinny dip
directions: Mix in blender, then add 1 1/2 teaspoons parsley flakes.
Mix well.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Whip softened cream cheese with electric mixer until soft and smooth.
Add other ingredients.
Serve with favorite veggies.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix flour, pecans and oleo together and press in pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Mix next 4 ingredients and pour on crust.
Top with pie filling.

title: scripture cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar; stir until fluffy.
Stir in eggs.
Sift about 1/4 cup of flour mixture in bowl and mix well.
Stir in about 1/3 cup of water.
Add remainder of flour and water, alternately, stirring between each addition until smooth.
Follow Solomon's advice for making good men out of growing boys (Proverbs 23:13) and beat well by hand at least 8 to 10 minutes.
Add honey, raisins, chopped figs and walnuts.
Stir well until mixed.
Bake at 350° in a 10-inch greased tube pan for 90 minutes.

title: pasta salad italian
directions: In large bowl, blend Italian dressing, mustard and pepper. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover.
Chill thoroughly. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil, then simmer for about 30 minutes or until onion is cooked.
This is enough to baste 2 chickens.

title: cold sesame noodles(from gourmet magazine)
directions: In a saucepan, combine soy sauce, vinegar, pepper flakes, brown sugar, peanut butter, oil, ginger and broth.
Simmer the mixture, stirring, until thick and smooth.
Let cool slightly.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: new orleans spicy shrimp
directions: Melt butter in saute pan.
Add onions, scallion tops, garlic and parsley and saute until onions are translucent.
Add shrimp, Old Bay seasoning (as much or as little as you prefer, approximately 2 tablespoons) and flour; stir.
Add wine and simmer until shrimp is cooked (bright pink).
Add cream; bring to boil. Spoon over 2 slices French bread.
Garnish with more fresh parsley.

title: sugar and fat-free fruit salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges.
Heat a cup of the juice from the other fruits to boil.
Add hot juice to bowl with Jell-O.
Cool by adding the rest of the juice.
Add the fruits.
In a small bowl, mix the vanilla pudding (instant) with the orange juice to make a paste; mix with the fruit.
Add 2 sliced bananas.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Good!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, peanuts, Karo, water and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring continuously until peanuts are very brown (or to the hard crack stage on a candy thermometer).
Add soda and stir.
Pour in buttered pan.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole(serves 8)
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup, curry and lemon juice to make a sauce.
Mix the Pepperidge Farm dressing with melted oleo.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: You will need 1 large pot.

title: chipped beef
directions: Saute pecans in butter to place on top before putting in oven. Put dried beef in blender and chop very fine.
Mix all ingredients with hands.
Shape into a ball.
Put pecans on top and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: This is the best apple cake I have ever tasted.

title: broiled veggies
directions: Preheat broiler to 550°.
Place eggplant on rack and brush with oil.
Season with herbs, if desired.
Broil for 5 minutes. Turn and oil.
Broil for 3 minutes or add a topping of thick sauce and cheese.
Arrange mushrooms on rack.
Put olive oil inside each.
Broil 4 minutes.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Cut dates and add to boiling water and soda; stand aside.
Mix all dry ingredients; add egg, vanilla, butter and nuts, then add water and dates.
Mix.
Bake in a loaf pan that has been greased and floured for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
I start to check it at 55 minutes, sometimes it's done in an hour.
Excellent served with cream cheese.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Place apples and 1/4 cup sugar in a greased casserole.
In a medium bowl, mix butter and remaining brown sugar until smooth. Add egg and milk.
Combine flour and baking powder; spread mixture evenly over apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: low-fat cranberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease 12 muffin cups. Stir together all ingredients, except cranberries, until moistened. Stir in cranberries. Fill muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pan immediately. Makes 12 muffins.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and put in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix ingredients (minus paraffin and chocolate chips) and roll into small balls.
Refrigerate balls for 2 hours before dipping. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler until liquified.
Drop balls and coat in chocolate well!
Place balls onto waxed paper and store in refrigerator.
Makes 48 small balls or 24 large ones.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach into bits. Toss with ingredients and dressing. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocomint balls
directions: Beat softened shortening and egg yolk until thoroughly blended.
Add the candy cane and cake mix and mix.
Roll into golf ball size balls and place on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes or until no impression is left when lightly touched.
Remove to cooling rack immediately and sprinkle with powdered sugar when cooled.

title: baked quesadilla squares
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with Pam.
Sprinkle cheese in bottom.
Top with chilies.
Combine milk, baking mix and eggs in large bowl and beat until smooth.
Carefully pour over chilies. Top with 1/4 cup salsa.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes until puffed and golden.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with sour cream, guacamole and salsa.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour the 1 cup of boiling water over the all-bran, bran buds and raisins.
Mix first 7 ingredients together, then add bran mixture.
Mix real good.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Cover and keep mixture in the icebox for up to 6 weeks.
Make muffins whenever you want to.
Always stir mixture before baking.

title: green beans supreme
directions: In skillet simmer onion in butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well and add sour cream.
Blend with cooked beans. Pour into a shallow baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: shirley's vegetable beef soup
directions: In a large pot or kettle, cook meat in 6 cups cold water, simmering about 2 hours until meat comes off bones. Remove meat and bones from broth and set aside to cool.
Return meat to stock when cool enough to remove from bones.

title: double-clutching manicotti
directions: Prepare the noodles per instructions on the package; use olive oil and garlic salt in the water to boil the noodles in.

title: kraut chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water to egg mixture.
Stir in kraut.
Turn into two greased and floured 8-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tests done. Fill and frost with Mocha Whipped Cream.

title: black and white chips
directions: Beat until fluffy all ingredients together (except flour and chips) with a mixer.
Stir in the flour, then stir in the chocolate chips.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, mix together sugar, flour, cocoa and salt. Separate eggs.
Add yolks and milk.
Cook on medium heat until it thickens and boils.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff, beat in sugar.
Top pie and bake at 350° until brown.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in bowl until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes in shallow baking or roasting pan; discard bag.

title: chocolate dream bars
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with 1/2 of graham crackers.
Reserve rest for topping.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in melted chocolate that has been slightly cooled.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread mixture into pan and sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with ice cream.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: take your choice bread(no fat)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin, bananas or zucchini, applesauce, egg substitute and water; mix.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch pan with nonstick spray or use muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: crunchy celery casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 3 ingredients and put in an 8-inch casserole dish.
In the microwave, saute the almonds with the margarine for about 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour almonds over the crushed crackers and toss lightly.
Spread cracker mixture over celery mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Heat 7-Up; stir in jello until dissolved.
Mix with applesauce and refrigerate until firm.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Select good size shrimp.
Precook bacon so it is still not all the way done.
Cut bacon big enough to wrap around the shrimp, holding together with toothpicks.
Place aluminum foil on grill and spray with Pam.
Mix ketchup and horseradish to taste.
Place on grill to cook with sauce.
Enjoy!!

title: broccoli rice cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown onion in butter. Mix soup, cheese whiz and broccoli with onion and butter until broccoli thaws. Add rice and mix well. Pour into a 9 x 11-inch greased casserole dish. Bake for 25-30 minutes covered. Remove foil for last 10 minutes to brown on top, if desired.

title: pork in apple cider stew(serves 6)
directions: Dredge pork in flour.
Heat oil in saute pan and brown pork quickly.
Drain pork on paper towel.
Drain oil.

title: christiana campbell's tavern sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins that are 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Puree sweet potatoes in blender.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat egg into the potatoes.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add the dry ingredients alternating by hand with milk, chopped nuts and raisins, mixing just until blended.
Do not overmix.
Spoon into greased muffin tins, filling each tin completely full.
A little sugar and cinnamon may be sprinkled on top of each muffin.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: first rate chocolate pie
directions: Mix
flour,
cocoa, sugar and salt.
Stir in egg yolks. Add milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake until brown about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: german leek soup
directions: Dice onion,
leeks,
bacon
and
mushrooms and saute in oleo. Add
cooked
and
diced carrots, potatoes and broccoli. Add water and
bouillon cubes and simmer 1 hour.
Add 8 ounces cream cheese and simmer until melted.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Cook spinach in microwave about 6 to 7 minutes.
Drain.
Mix spinach with all ingredients.
Cook in casserole dish about 5 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together sugar and eggs. Dissolve soda in applesauce and add salt, cinnamon and cloves with part of the flour and add to the first mixture. Add enough more flour to make a fairly stiff batter. Grease and flour pan and bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peppery beef
directions: Partially freeze beef.
Cut on the bias into thin bite size strips.
For marinade, combine soy sauce, sugar, 1 tablespoon of the oil, garlic, pepper and red pepper.
Stir in beef.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: stir-fry northern pike
directions: Preheat wok or large frypan.
Coat with 1 tablespoon margarine and 1 tablespoon oil (add more oil if needed).
Stir-fry hard vegetables (celery, broccoli, chestnuts) first.
Push aside. Next, stir-fry other vegetables (onion, pepper, snow peas).
Push aside.
Add fish.
Cook until flaky.
Add any desired seasoning (thyme, sage, salt) during cooking.
Serve over rice with soy sauce.
Serves 3 large or 4 medium servings.

title: pepper steak with mushrooms
directions: Brown beef cubes in shortening and remove from pan.
Blend in flour to make a paste.
Add catsup, water, soy sauce, bouillon, garlic, onion and green peppers; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add beef to sauce; simmer until tender. Add mushrooms.
Cook until crisp-tender.
Serve over hot, fluffy rice.

title: salmon pate
directions: Line a 2-cup bowl or loaf pan with plastic wrap.
Blend ingredients.
Press into bowl and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with crackers or cucumber slices.

title: color cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: unusual popovers
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls into hot grease. They will brown on one side and then pop over.
You can sprinkle with sugar, if desired.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onions in Dutch oven size pan.
Add beans, tomatoes, corn, seasoning and 3 cans of water.
(Use cans that beans came in.)
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for about 5 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Do not peel apples.
Cut apples and celery into bite-size pieces.
Mix all ingredients in large salad bowl.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: cocktail pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers in water and lime for 24 hours.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Let stand in cold water 3 hours and drain off.
Pour syrup of sugar, vinegar, mustard and celery seed and salt over cucumbers and let stand overnight.
Put on stove and cook for 30 minutes and then seal while hot.
These are always crisp and you can use any size cucumbers.
Weigh cucumbers after sliced.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, White Sauce, salt and pepper in greased casserole bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese. Mix bread crumbs and butter.
Put on top of mixture. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh green bean soup
directions: Clean and cut beans into 1 inch lengths.
Wash thoroughly. Cook beans and onion in water until beans are tender.
Add potatoes and cook 20 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet; add flour and cook until browned.
Pour into soup.
Cook on medium for 5 minutes.
Mix sour cream with 1 cup cold water until milk-like. Set aside.
Remove soup from heat.
Let cool 1/2 hour.
Pour sour cream mixture slowly into soup, stirring constantly.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons white vinegar to soup.
Return to heat.
Bring soup to a boil and remove from heat.
Serve hot.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Combine with pepper in a 2-quart microwave casserole.
Cook on High 6 to 8 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring once.
Drain, cover and set aside.
For sauce, combine liquid Butter Buds, 1/4 cup flour, bouillon, pepper, milk and water in a saucepan and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheese.
In the casserole, combine chicken, peppers, cooked spaghetti, mushrooms and sauce. May sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Cook on High for 1 to 3 minutes until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add remaining ingredients.

title: dilly bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat egg into yeast and water mixture.
In a large bowl, combine warm cottage cheese, sugar, butter, onion, dill seed, salt and soda into egg and yeast combination.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Beat well.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender and falls off bone.
Cool, then debone and skin.
Cut into 1/2 to 1 inch chunks to equal 2 1/2 cups chicken.
Add celery, grapes and almonds to the chicken. Mix with mayo or salad dressing and sour cream.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: advent crescents
directions: Sift flour and salt into a bowl.
Mix in sugar and almonds. Make a well in the center.
Add butter, egg yolks and extract to the well.
Mix well using hands.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into tiny balls, then make ropes out of each ball.
Place on cookie sheet and curve each into a crescent shape.
Bake until lightly brown.
Cool; roll in powdered sugar.

title: m & m holiday party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars in large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture, blending well.
Stir in 1/2 c. of candies.

title: easy italian pork dinner
directions: Marinate pork chops in 1/4 cup salad dressing in baking dish for 3 hours.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Return to marinade. Layer potatoes and onion over chops.
Dot with butter.
Drizzle with 2 tablespoons salad dressing.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix avocados, lemon juice, garlic salt and salt.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies, stirred, until dip is thick enough for dip and not too runny.
Drop avocado pits into dip to keep from turning brown.

title: no sugar applesauce cake
directions: Combine and cook raisins with 2 cups water until raisins have used up all water (cook slowly).
Set aside to cool.
In large bowl, mix flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine eggs, applesauce, equal oil and vanilla.
Add nuts and fruit mixture.
Stir in dry ingredients and blend thoroughly. Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender and break into pieces. Add all of the soups and Veg all and mix together. Add broth, salt and pepper to taste. Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts. Put on top 2 more pie crusts and bake until brown.

title: orange cream cheese bread
directions: Combine cream cheese and shortening, creaming well.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well and stir in walnuts and orange rind.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle orange juice over loaves.
Remove to wire racks to finish cooling.

title: sandies
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine until softened.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add water and vanilla and beat well.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls or 1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch fingers.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 20 minutes or until done. Remove and cool.
In a plastic bag gently shake a few at a time in powdered sugar.
Makes about 45.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Boil zucchini squash and slice 1-inch thick.
Drain.
Put in pan with cheese and sauce.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage medley
directions: Stir dressing and water into skillet (with about 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil).
Add vegetables, stirring to coat well. Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes.

title: corn bake
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes, if you would like, and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked ham strata(makes 8 servings)
directions: Toast bread and spread on one side of each with butter.
Cut toast into 3/4-inch pieces.

title: kardemomme kaker(cardamom holiday cookies)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture.
Dough should be stiff.
More flour may be added if necessary to make dough easier to handle.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll dough very thin; cut in squares and rounds.
Brush tops of cookies with milk; sprinkle with almonds and sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 9 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: five cup salad
directions: In a bowl, combine mandarin oranges, pineapple chunks, coconut, marshmallows and sour cream.
Cover and chill for several hours or overnight.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 2 cups crushed corn flakes or Rice Krispies.
Drizzle 1/4 cup melted butter over these.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients and combine the 2 mixtures.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Can serve plain or with powdered sugar sifted over it.

title: egg yolk frosting
directions: Place egg yolks, tartar, salt, water, lemon juice and sugar in the top of a double boiler.
Place over boiling water (upper pan should not touch water).
Beat with a rotary or electric mixer for 7 minutes or until mixture is thick and fluffy and holds its shape.
Stir in lemon rind and spread on cake.
This icing especially suitable for a white cake as well as Sunshine Cake.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Combine with vegetables.
Boil sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves.
Pour over vegetables while hot. Serves 6.

title: low-fat oat bran muffins
directions: Combine oat bran, flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and allspice.
In a small bowl, whisk together milk, preserves and egg whites.
Pour liquid ingredients over the flour mixture.
Stir to moisten.
Fold in raisins.
Line 14 cups with liners.
Fill with batter.
Bake at 350° for 22 minutes or until brown and firm.
Contains 108 calories and 1.4 fat.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, celery soup, mushroom soup, cottage cheese, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and onion together.
Pour into a large or 2 small casserole dishes.
Mix together Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 40 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: dietetic date cookies
directions: Combine in saucepan the raisins, dates and water.
Boil together 3 minutes, stirring constantly, then cool.
Cream together eggs, margarine, sweetener and vanilla.
Sift together cinnamon, flour and soda.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with date mixture.
Beat well.
Chill several hours.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: In a saucepan melt butter.
Add flour.
Stir to combine.
Add fish bouillon a little at a time stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Add half & half.
Bring to a boil.
Cook uncovered for about 4 minutes.
Add whipping cream, paprika, tomato puree or paste and brandy or sherry.
Bring to a boil again, whisking constantly.
Add peas and shrimp.
Heat to serving temperature. Ladle soup into soup bowls.
Garnish with small dill sprigs and a few peeled shrimp.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix well.
Let mixture chill overnight.
This is great with fish.
Store in jar in refrigerator.
Great with fish or hot dogs on sandwiches.

title: chicken soup-bulgaria(pileshka soopa)
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and saut in oil.
Take out.
Saut onions.
When soft, add red pepper, mix in salt and 1 quart water, bring to a boil.
Add chicken and simmer until soft.
Add 1/4 cup water to a boil with flour, stirring until flour is mixed thoroughly.
Add flour mixture to soup and stir well.
Serves 6.

title: company potatoes
directions: Combine all but last two ingredients and pour in casserole. Top with sliced almonds and drizzle with butter or margarine. Bake 15 minutes at 400° and then broil until brown on top.

title: bratwurst with applekraut(crockpot recipe)
directions: In a crockery cooker, stir together all ingredients.
Stir in 1/4 cup of water.
Cover and cook on low heat setting for 3 or 4 hours.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat the water, vinegar, oil and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Drain kraut; rinse several times in water and squeeze until dry.
Add all ingredients and stir well.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Mash bananas and applesauce together.
Add dry ingredients to mixture and add coffee.
Blend in jam and add nuts.
Cook in a tube pan for 2 1/2 hours at 275°. Frost with your favorite caramel frosting.

title: yeast bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, yeast and salt. Heat water, milk, margarine until very warm. Add to dry ingredients, beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Add 1/2 cup flour and 2 eggs. Continue beating another 2 minutes on high speed. With wooden spoon add 3 to 4 cups flour. Turn out onto floured surface kneading dough for 8 minutes. Cover with paper towel and let rest for 20 minutes. Divide dough into half, and place each half into a greased loaf pan. Cover and let rise until double in size. Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown. If you prefer, this will make 24 rolls, rather than the loaves.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender, about 15 minutes. Add consomme and water and 1/2 teaspoon salt; heat over medium heat for about 5 minutes.
Place cheese in 3 bowls.
Pour soup over cheese and add about 1/2 cup croutons to each bowl.

title: texas torte
directions: Add flour, salt and milk to eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in a 10 x 15-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white batter bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and oleo (or butter).
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large bowl; sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture.
Stir in flour; batter will be fairly stiff.
Beat until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 40 minutes.
Stir batter down real good; pour into 2 greased loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Let rise until double, then bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and pineapple and let stand overnight. Bring to a boil and cook 20 minutes.
Take off stove immediately and add the two boxes of strawberry Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved. Seal in hot jars.

title: mrs. deen's chocolate cake
directions: Best if mixed by hand.
Mix all ingredients.
I put in a sheet cake or Bundt pan.
I prefer the Bundt.
Does not need any icing. Very rich.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into a ball. Roll in chopped pecans. Refrigerate.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Boil together 7-Up, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuits thin. Put apples in the middle.
Pull dough up around the apples.
Pinch dough together.
Place in baking dish.
Pour 7-Up mixture over the apple dumplings and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: garlic, oil and romano cheese spaghetti
directions: Brown garlic in pan with oil.
Put parsley in pan with garlic-oil mixture; stir.
Cook spaghetti; rinse.
Pour garlic mixture over spaghetti and toss.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese and toss again.
Serve.

title: buttermilk sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and add enough flour to roll. Roll and cut.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix sugar, water, Kool-Aid and pineapple juice together. Freeze.
Take out 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: pesto vegetables
directions: Cook and drain vegetables as directed on package. Toss vegetables and pesto. Sprinkle with cheese.
This has 7 grams carbohydrates.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in large casserole dish.
Stir in all ingredients. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in pineapple juice and orange juice.
Add water, sugar and lemon juice.
Stir well. Just before serving, add cans of soda.
Serves 20.

title: jim's venison jerky (beef)
directions: This recipe makes enough to marinate at least 3 pounds of venison or beef.
In a glass or plastic container, mix all ingredients.
Marinate meat strips overnight.
Remove from liquid. Pat dry with paper towels.
Place on cookie sheet in a single layer and place in oven at 200° for 6 to 8 hours or until dry by feel.

title: quick onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place half of the onions on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that has been coated with nonstick vegetable spray.
Layer with the crushed crackers, sausage, remaining onions, soup, salt and cheese.
Bake for 1 hour, until golden, and serve.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: lo-cal potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets in boiling, salted water, in a large kettle until tender; drain.
Cool, peel and cube.
Toss potatoes and dressing in large bowl until coated.
Chop and add hard pickle.

title: baby cheese cakes
directions: In large bowl mix all ingredients except vanilla wafers.
Mix until smooth. Put muffin papers in muffin pan.
Put vanilla wafer in each, then top with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Chill, then top with cherries or blueberries.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in a pan and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Mix together the remaining ingredients together well.
Shape into loaf and place in shallow pan.
Pour the 1/2 cup sauce mixture over meat loaf.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: patricia's chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients well in mixing bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into uncooked pie shells.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip when cool.

title: pastrami ball
directions: Chop meat and mix with rest of ingredients.
Shape into ball and chill.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: gingerbread
directions: Grease and lightly flour 13 x 9-inch pan. In large bowl, cream Crisco and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat 1 minute.

title: blue ribbon chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt; mix well with wire whisk.
Set aside.
Blend sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add the flour mixture and chocolate chips.
Mix everything together.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: shanty potatoes
directions: Place potatoes, margarine, oil and onion in a large skillet. Add water to cover.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover; cook over medium heat until potatoes are done (they will be thick like gravy) adding water as needed and stirring occasionally.

title: party punch
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a large punch bowl; mix well.
Put sherbet on top.

title: 2 minute basic mayonnaise
directions: Combine egg, salt, lemon juice and 1/4 cup Wesson oil in blender container.
Blend together until mixture begins to thicken. Blend in remaining 3/4 cup oil, pouring in a thin stream until mixture is thick and smooth, about 2 minutes.
Makes 1 cup.

title: spam casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole dish that's been buttered, except cheese.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Add cheese the last 10 minutes of cooking time.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Cook pork roast in crock-pot. Take out. Cut up pork taking fat out. Drain juice. Put pork back in empty crock-pot. Add sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and red crushed pepper to taste. Also add hot sauce or barbecue sauce. Pour about 1 to 1 1/2 cups of juice back over pork. Cook on low about 6 to 8 hours. The longer it cooks without drying out, the better it is.

title: cheese and fruit kugel
directions: Mix all
together (except fruit cocktail).
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan
(greased).
Top
with fruit cocktail and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese enchiladas(enchiladas de queso)
directions: Prepare sauce.
Heat in a medium saucepan.
Reserve 1/3 cheese for topping.
Heat oil in a medium pan.
Soften one side of tortilla; quickly turn to soften other side, 3 to 5 seconds.
Drain on paper towels.
Immediately dip tortilla in hot sauce.
Remove at once.
Place on plate and arrange either flat or rolled.
Sprinkle cheese with chopped onion and place in a shallow medium baking dish.
Cover with sauce and rest of cheese.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain. Meanwhile in skillet, combine onions and ground beef, stirring constantly until onions are tender and meat is browned.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, pepper and salt.
Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Stir noodles into beef mixture.
Turn into casserole and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Add confectioners sugar.
Beat.
Can be thinned with canned milk.

title: creamy cornbread
directions: Grease baking pan with part of the oil.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in a large pan for 30 minutes or until golden brown and firm.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: date nut cookies
directions: Mix all of ingredients.
Make golf-size balls.
Bake 10 to 11 minutes at 375°.
Remove immediately.
Cookies are very delicious and crisp.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs in mixing bowl, add oil and sugar, mixing well. Sift dry ingredients together and add in portions to egg mixture. Add vanilla and baby food carrots.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured) in 300° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
May substitute jar carrots with 2 cups grated carrots.

title: spicy oven pork chops
directions: About 1/4 hours before serving:
In large open roasting pan, mix soy sauce, sherry and water.
Place pork chops in soy sauce mixture, turning each chop to coat well.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
With pastry brush, baste chops occasionally with soy sauce mixture in pan.
Meanwhile, in 2-quart pan, over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook onion until done.
Mix with other ingredients and pour over pork chops when done.

title: hanover's brisket
directions: Combine ingredients, all but barbecue sauce, pour over meat and marinate overnight.
Bake in liquid for 4 hours for 4 pounds or 5 hours for 5 pounds at 300°.
Baste occasionally during baking. Cover until last hour and then remove cover and pour cup barbecue sauce over and increase temperature to 350°.

title: family favorite burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 6 patties, each about 3/4-inch thick.
Set oven control to broil and/or 550°.
Broil with tops 4 inches from heat, turning once to desired doneness, 10 to 15 minutes.
Top with American or Cheddar cheese.
Serves 6.

title: hamburg-casserole
directions: In casserole dish, layer hamburg, sliced potatoes, carrots, hamburg, potatoes and carrots.
Pour soup mix over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until potatoes and carrots are done.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Brush a 10-inch spring-form pan with soft butter. Coat the pan with the superfine sugar; lightly tap out excess sugar and set pan aside. Combine 1 cup butter and remaining 2 cups superfine sugar in a bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment. Beat on medium speed, scraping down the sides with a rubber spatula until mixture is light and fluffy, about 5 minutes. Carefully fold in applesauce. Do not overmix. Sift together 2 3/4 cups flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg, cloves, salt and baking powder. Fold the dry ingredients and pecans into the applesauce mixture. Add vanilla, brandy and apple slices and mix until combined. Transfer batter to the prepared spring-form pan.

title: butterscotch nutbread
directions: *Sour Milk Mix:
Combine 1 tablespoon lemon juice or vinegar and milk to total 1 cup.
Let stand 5 minutes before using in recipe.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Partially cook potatoes in microwave and set aside.
Place cooked chicken in 9x15 inch casserole dish.
Add cooked potato cubes and frozen vegetables.
Mix and heat soup, broth and onion. Pour soup mixture over chicken and vegetables.
In a small bowl, mix milk, melted margarine, and biscuit mix.
(You may want to use more biscuit mix and add milk until pouring consistency.)
Pour batter over all ingredients in casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter until smooth. Pour cereal in pan and coat with chocolate mixture.
Put powdered sugar in a large brown paper bag, then add the cereal mixture. Shake well.
Pour into a bowl.
Keep covered.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop and use 1/3 cup stems. Saute stems, onion and green pepper in 3 tablespoons of the margarine.
Mix in remainder of ingredients, then stuff caps.
Use remaining 1 tablespoon margarine to grease pan and place caps in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet sour meat balls
directions: Mix well together.
Mold into tiny balls.
Broil for 10 to 12 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: four day coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar, frozen coconut and sour cream and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, prepare cake according to directions on box, making two layers.
When cool, split in two, making four layers. Put together with sour cream and coconut mixture.
Cover top and sides with one can of Angel Flake coconut.
Refrigerate
three to four days before cutting.

title: johnny marzetti casserole
directions: Saute vegetables and meat in butter; add salt and cook about 5 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain and add olives and sauce to vegetable mix.
Cover noodles; top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 20 people.

title: poppin' fresh barbecups
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef; drain. Add barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Separate biscuit dough into 12 biscuits. Place one in each of 12 ungreased muffin cups, pressing dough up sides to edge of cup. Spoon meat into cups.
Sprinkle each with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: beef stew casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 5 1/2 hours at 250°.
Do not open oven and do not open casserole during baking time.

title: back home corn bread salad
directions: In a large bowl, crumble corn muffins.
Add mayonnaise, green pepper, onion and celery.
Fold in tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste. Break fried, drained bacon into small pieces for topping.

title: white (light) fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well; put into greased pan.
Cook at 325° until well done.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in greased pan 30 to 40 minutes or until browned.

title: camper's pizza
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in well-seasoned 11 to 12-inch heavy skillet with heatproof handle over medium coals until no longer pink, stirring occasionally to break up beef.
Remove beef mixture to paper towel.
Season with salt.
Pour off drippings, leaving skillet "greased."
Separate crescent roll dough triangles.
Place in skillet, pressing edges together to form bottom crust and 1-inch rim up side of skillet.
Spread half of pizza sauce over dough. Spoon ground beef mixture over sauce.
Top with mushrooms, olives and bell pepper.
Pour remaining sauce over all.
Sprinkle with cheese and oregano.
Place skillet in center of grid over medium coals.
Place cover on cooker and cook 20 to 30 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour 1/2 batter into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 of cheese.
Pour remaining batter and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: apple delicious
directions: Place sliced apples in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan; set aside. Place water in saucepan.
Mix spices, sugar and clear jel.
Make paste by using a little water in saucepan, then add to water. Bring to a boil.
Pour over apples.
Pour the cake mix over apple mixture.
Shred the stick of oleo over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese cake surprise(makes own crust as it bakes)
directions: Beat cheese until well beaten.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add sugar and extract.
Beat until smooth, thick and lemon colored.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes.

title: keebler cookie salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and pudding mix together.
Fold in Cool Whip, oranges and pineapple.
Crush 1/2 the package of cookies and fold them into salad.
Crush a few more cookies and sprinkle them over top just before serving.

title: no bake chocolate squares
directions: Microwave milk and chips for about 40 seconds. Stir until smooth; add vanilla. Combine Graham wafer crumbs and confectioners sugar; add to chocolate mixture and mix well. Press evenly in 8-inch or 9-inch square pan. Chill.

title: basic creole dressing mix
directions: Grind meat.
Melt margarine in a Dutch oven and fry meat until brown, about 20 minutes.
Add onions, celery and garlic.
Stir and cook until soft.
Add Worcestershire sauce, bouillon and 1 stick margarine.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 2 hours.
Season to taste.
Serves 12.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cheese pie
directions: Put everything in a blender and blend until smooth.
Spray no-stick on aluminum pie pan . No need for pie crust.
Pour mixture into pie pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until knife comes out clean.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop with spoon in hot grease; brown.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into jar and shake for a minute.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake before using.

title: general tso's chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in eggs, cornstarch and 1/2 tablespoon sesame oil for 1 hour (refrigerate).
Fry in hot peanut oil.
Remove. Allow oil to heat again and fry once more until golden.
Heat pan. Add 1 ounce oil.
Cook for a bit.
Add a dash or two or hot oil. Add remaining ingredients to thicken and add chicken.
Heat and serve with steamed broccoli and steamed white rice.

title: blue cheese corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Combine all ingredients; mix until blended.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake until firm to touch and golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut into squares and serve warm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pink panther salad
directions: Mix pie filling and milk.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: cheese blues
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Place in two round cake pans.
Melt butter and Blue cheese.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot.

title: sweet and sour beef tips
directions: In 3-quart saucepan or Dutch oven, brown half the meat at a time.
When all meat is browned return to pan.
Stir in next 10 ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for 1 1/2 hours or until desired tenderness.
Blend cornstarch and water.
Stir into sauce mixture and cook until it is thick and bubbly.
Serve with cooked noodles.
Garnish with carrot curls and a little parsley.
Easy but good!

title: chicken spaghetti with rotel tomatoes
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in skillet and saute medium chopped onion and bell pepper (optional) until tender.
Add the Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of chicken soup and Cheddar cheese.
Add chopped chicken and drained spaghetti.
Keep heat low until the cheese melts.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole and bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry nut gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry and lemon gelatins in boiling water.
Add cold water, pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Stir in cranberry sauces, crushed pineapple, applesauce and walnut meats.
Pour into a 7 1/2 x 11-inch pan or 10-cup gelatin mold.
Allow to set until firm.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk. Blend well. Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Reduce heat and cook stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool slightly and set aside.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add gelatin and beat well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Yields 12 servings. Use a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Take raisins and water, boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients with 1/3 cup liquid from raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet and bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields about seven dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes in boiling salted water.
Drain well.
Combine all but crackers, cheese and margarine.
Pour broccoli mixture in 2-quart casserole bowl.
Sprinkle top with cheese, then on top of cheese sprinkle with crackers and dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zwieback(double buns)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and sugar. Let stand 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. The dough will be softer than bread dough. (When the dough no longer sticks to the bread board on which it is being kneaded, it will have enough flour.) Let rise until double in bulk.
