Pinch off small balls of dough and place on a greased baking sheet. Then place a smaller ball on top of each bun. Press down to help seal. Let rise until double. Bake at 375° about 15 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: layered salad
directions: In a bowl, layer the ingredients in order listed, spreading the mayonnaise, salt and sugar over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: herb mustard rub(for pork, beef, lamb and kebabs before roasting)
directions: In a small bowl, combine onion, mustard, marjoram, rosemary and black pepper.
Spread this herb mixture on all sides of the roast (up to 3 pounds).
Cover and refrigerate from 2 to 24 hours before meat is roasted or grilled.

title: zucchini bread or muffins
directions: For one 17 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan (48 brownies), you will need:

title: apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
Combine sugar, flour (or tapioca) and cinnamon; mix with apples.
Line pie pan with shell and fill with apples.
Top with crust.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until apples are done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight.
Serve with pumpernickel bread or rye.
Hollow out bread and place dip in hollow.
Place torn pieces from center around loaf.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown meat and onion, then add rest of ingredients and simmer one half to 2 hours.

title: spinach gnocchis
directions: Heat 1/4-inch of water in a large saucepan over high heat until boiling.
Cook spinach, tossing quickly until wilted, about 1 minute.
Drain and allow to cool slightly; squeeze out as much liquid as possible.
Chop very fine and set aside.

title: cornbread for a chili supper
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
Beat the eggs; add the milk and melted butter.
Add the dry ingredients and stir well.
Spread the batter in a buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Cook in a preheated 375° oven for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned around the edges.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Spoon into two graham cracker pie crusts.
Cool.
Top with strawberries.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift together flour and salt; add shortening and cut until mixture resembles corn meal.
Combine egg, vinegar and water and add flour mixture.
Stir lightly with a fork until dough follows fork in the bowl.
Form into 4 balls and chill.
Makes two 9-inch double pie crusts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of 11 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix soups and milk and pour on top of rice, mixing a little with a fork. Place cut-up chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours or 275° for 3 hours.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello; cool to lukewarm.
Add raspberries and applesauce.
Let set.

title: tomato, mozzarella and basil salad
directions: Slice Mozzarella cheese and tomatoes thinly.
Arrange on a platter, alternating tomato and Mozzarella cheese slices.
Chop fresh basil and sprinkle on top of tomatoes.
Drizzle Italian dressing over all.

title: easy bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add melted butter; mix thoroughly.
Add sugar, vanilla and milk.
Mix in bread cubes.
Add raisins, if desired. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: eggs goldenrod
directions: In saucepan, simmer cream for 10 minutes to thicken slightly. Reduce heat to low and gradually add cheese, stirring constantly until it is melted; set aside.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Sprinkle the cabbage, onion and green pepper with sugar; don't stir.

title: chinese salad
directions: Combine
ingredients
in
a
small
bowl
or jar with a cover. Sauce needs to be mixed thoroughly or shaken vigorously in jar.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine sour cream and baking soda; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Mix.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with sour cream mixture.
Pour in 9-inch greased pan.

title: apricot-orange freeze
directions: Line muffin tins with paper baking cups.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Fill baking cups and freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature a few minutes before serving.

title: grandma's chocolate pie
directions: In top of a double boiler, sift together cocoa, flour, sugar and salt.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with beaten egg whites for meringue.
Bake until meringue is golden brown.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix last two ingredients together.
Soften yeast in warm water in mixing bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon of sugar and let stand 5 minutes to activate yeast.
Add shortening, potatoes and 2 cups of flour in bowl together, along with eggs and sugar.
Then add enough flour to make come away from the bowl (just slightly stick to the touch of the finger).
Put in a greased plastic bag.
Add 1 teaspoon of oil to inside of bag.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Bring out and turn onto a floured pastry cloth or cabinet top.
Flatten to 1/2-inch.
Cut into desired shapes and place on greased cookie sheets.
Let double in bulk for about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: green chili stew
directions: In
large heavy saucepan cook meat until no longer red. Drain. Add
salt
and flour; blend over low heat.
Add water; increase heat
to
medium.
Add
potatoes,
onion, beef base, garlic
and salt.
Cook
until potatoes are cooked not mushy. Add chopped green chili to taste. Boil for 1 minute more, then serve.

title: deviled scallops
directions: Simmer scallops in small amount of water for 2 to 3 minutes if small scallops and 5 minutes if larger.
Drain and save liquid. Cut up scallops and add to butter which is creamed with seasonings and 1/3 cup reserved liquid.
Let stand 1/2 hour in baking dish. Cover with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: company's coming cashew pie
directions: Prepare pie crust for a 9-inch pie.
Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat the brown sugar and margarine at high speed until fluffy.
Add corn syrup and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Stir in cashew nuts.
Pour into crust lined pie pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until top of pie is deep golden brown.
Cover edge of crust with strips of foil after 15 to 20 minutes of baking to prevent excessive browning.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jalapeno turkey
directions: Season turkey well with salt, pepper, poultry seasoning, Season-All and cayenne pepper.
Stuff turkey with celery, onions, bell peppers, jalapeno peppers and sausage.
Place in foil lined heavy roaster and pour on turkey salad dressing, beer, white wine and vinegar.
Cover with foil and cook on grill with full bag of charcoal 4 to 6 hours or in 400° oven.
Baste every 30 to 40 minutes.

title: savory sausage and rice casserole
directions: Break apart sausage and brown in ungreased skillet, pouring off excess fat.
Remove from burner.

title: beth's baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until limp (half done).
Remove from pan and saute onion in bacon grease.
Cut up bacon and mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken broccoli delight
directions: Brown the chicken until done. Thaw vegetables and lightly saute.
In a large casserole dish, add chicken in bottom and cover with vegetables.
Add the cream of broccoli soup and milk.
Stir to mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 375° until bubbly.

title: gracie's easy homemade bread
directions: Warm sugar, shortening, 2 cups water and salt in microwave until shortening is dissolved and let cool.
Combine yeast, sugar and 3/4 cup warm water.
Let rise for 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together with egg.
Add 1 cup at a time
the flour, 7 to 8 cups flour in all.
Grease same bowl and let rise until doubled.
Punch down dough and make into bread or rolls and let rise once again.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Combine ground beef, refried beans, oregano and cumin; mix well.
Fill uncooked manicotti shells with meat mixture.
Arrange in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine water and picante sauce or taco sauce; pour over manicotti shells.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Micro-cook in a counter-top microwave oven on High for 10 minutes, giving dish a half-turn once.
Using tongs, turn shells over.
Micro-cook, covered, on Medium for 17 to 19 minutes or until pasta is tender, giving dish a half-turn once.
Combine sour cream, green onion and olives.
Spoon down center of casserole; top with cheese.
Micro-cook, uncovered, on High 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tropical shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Add enough ice cubes to measure 3 cups.
Blend until smooth. Serve immediately.
Makes 3 cups.

title: flying saucers
directions: Beat butter; gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg, molasses and milk; mix well. Combine flour and next 4 ingredients; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Shape dough into 2-inch balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets and flatten each ball with palm of hand.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheeets; remove to wire racks and cool completely. Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: celery bits
directions: Wash and trim stalks; cut into 1-inch pieces (about 12).
Mix remaining ingredients together in a bowl and spoon into celery pieces.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.

title: copper pennies
directions: Scrape and slice carrots.
Boil in salt water until tender. (Be sure not to overcook so they will hold their shape.)
Drain and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to carrots.
Mix well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well for several days. May be reheated or served cold.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients.
Add flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Drop on cookie sheet and top with greased and sugared glass.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Delicate and delicious.

title: old-fashioned peanut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a medium bowl, stir together flour, cornstarch and baking soda.
In a large bowl, beat butter for 10 seconds.
Beat in sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt. Beat until thick and light, about 1 min.
Add peanut butter.
Stir in flour mixture.
Using 1 1/2 Tbsp. dough for each cookie, roll into balls and arrange on a baking sheet, leaving 2-3 in. between each one.
Dip a fork into sugar and press on top of each cookie in two directions to flatten and make a crosshatch design.
Bake until golden brown around the edges, about 12 min.
Transfer to a rack and cool.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put the sugar into a saucepan; mix with the milk to form a thick paste.
Add the butter and stir in the grated or chopped chocolate.
Put the pan over low heat and cook, stirring constantly.

Do not let the contents of the saucepan come to a boil until the sugar has dissolved and the chocolate has melted. Then increase the heat slightly and let the mixture boil for about five minutes, or until it reaches the soft ball stage.
Take the fudge off the heat; beat it until it is thick and pour into an 8-inch square buttered pan.
Cut the fudge into 1-inch squares before it has time to get cold.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: unbaked fruitcake
directions: Roll graham crackers into crumbs.
Cut up marshmallows.
Chop nuts; add other ingredients.
Make into loaf and chill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Place crushed pineapples (do not drain) in a bowl.
Drain fruit cocktail, mandarin oranges and put with pudding mix.
Mix well. Sprinkle top with pecan pieces.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix peanut butter chips and butter over very low heat, just enough to soften, but not melt.
Take from heat and add marshmallows.
Mix together.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch foil pan. Cool, then cut.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Break into pieces and drain well. Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly with slight browning around the edges.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Crush Butterfingers and add to Cool Whip, chocolate milk and sweetened condensed milk.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: rum sauce for bread pudding
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in water and add hot milk, sugar and butter.
Stir until thick.
Remove from fire and add rum.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Dissolve soda in buttermilk, stirring well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with flour.
Add 1 cup mini-morsels, melted chocolate, chocolate syrup and vanilla, stirring just until blended.
(Do to overheat.)
Spoon batter into a heavily greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 to 35 minutes or until it springs back.
Remove from pan and cool.
Combine white chocolate and 2 tablespoons shortening in double boiler.
Bring water to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until mixture is melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Drizzle melted white chocolate mixture over cooled cake.
Melt remaining 1/2 cup mini-morsels and 2 teaspoons shortening in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Drizzle over white chocolate.
If desired, garnish with chocolate and white chocolate leaves.

title: barbecue cup
directions: Brown beef, onions and peppers in skillet.
Add barbecue sauce.
Simmer while fixing biscuits.
Mold biscuits in a greased muffin tin.
Fill with beef mixture.
Top with cheese and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown beef and add sauce.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion and green pepper. Put half noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese mixture, then add remaining noodles and pour beef mixture on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Make tomato sauce.
Cook lasagna noodles according to directions; drain.
Place in layers in 13 x 9-inch oblong pan, beginning and ending with tomato sauce.
Layer sauce, single layer of noodles and a mixture of last 6 ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve with meatballs, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tom's speedy eggnog
directions: Let ice cream melt slightly.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend well.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: old-fashioned jelly roll
directions: Sift
flour,
baking powder and salt; combine with eggs in bowl.
Beat with
rotary
beater;
turn
into
greased and floured pan.
Bake
in
hot oven at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Turn pan onto cloth, covered with confectioners sugar.
Spread with jelly. Roll at once.
Wrap in cloth.
Cool.
Now slice.

title: cider stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and thyme.
Toss with meat to coat.
In Dutch oven, brown meat in hot oil.
Stir in cider, water and vinegar.
Cook and stir to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until meat is tender 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add vegetables and apple.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to full boil the sugar, butter and milk.
Let boil for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat. Add Marshmallow Creme and blend well.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream together shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt; add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix butter, cocoa, and flour.
Then add sugar and milk.
Cook on medium heat until thick, stirring constantly because it will lump.
Serve with homemade biscuits.

title: jack-o-lantern jumble
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine together.
Stir in salt, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Put Rice Chex, Wheat Chex and peanuts in a 15 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Stir in other ingredients and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring several times. Take out of oven and cool on paper towels.
Add 1 1/2 cups of candy corn.

title: party mix
directions: In small microwave bowl, melt margarine on High.
Add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Mix cereals, nuts, pretzels and raisins in plastic bag.
Pour margarine mixture over and shake well, coating well.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring often.
Cool on absorbent paper to cool.
Cool in airtight container.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Put all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: peter paul cake
directions: Bake as directed in 3 or 4 layers.

title: ratatoulle
directions: Saving tomatoes:
You don't have to can that last batch of tomatoes from the garden or farmers' market.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for one hour or longer, if not baked in center of loaf when tested with toothpick.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Bring a large pot of water to boil.
Add salt and cook pasta for approximately 8 minutes or until al dente.
Drain and reserve. On two cookie sheets place all of the vegetables after cutting them into Julienne size pieces, 3x1/2 inches.
Cover with a light sprinkle of olive oil, salt, pepper and Italian seasonings.
Bake at 450 in oven for 20 minutes.
When completely cooked and pasta is ready, combine the pasta and vegetables in a large serving bowl.
Add the Parmigiana cheese and mix thoroughly.
Add the cherry tomatoes after cutting them in half.
Serve hot.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into 3-quart casserole and bake 30 minutes at 400° until bubbly hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain broccoli and spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken, soup, mayonnaise, mushrooms, curry powder and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese in a medium bowl.
Spread chicken mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over top.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil, stir and bake for 20 minutes more. Serves 6.

title: apple strudel
directions: Spread sour cream over fillo pastry.
Peel and core apples. Cut into slivers and arrange on top of sour cream.
Sprinkle with sugar, raisins and nuts.
If too liquidy, add bread crumbs.
Brush fillo dough sheet with butter (butter flavored Pam may be used). Place filling on fillo dough and roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place on buttered baking dish.
Brush with more butter.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and serve.

title: apricot-orange party tea
directions: Combine first six ingredients in saucepan.
Heat just to boiling.
Stir in tea.
Serve hot.

title: barbecue
directions: Saute onions.
Mash in corned beef.
Add other ingredients. Cook for 45 minutes or 1 hour.
Serve on rolls.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir well.
Alternate layers of chips, meat and cheese.
First and last layer should be chips.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and let cheese toast.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Combine cake mix and jello.
Add water, oil and flavoring. Blend with mixer while adding eggs, one at a time.
Blend well. Pour into a tube pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix; let stand, then roll and cut with inside of doughnut cutter.

title: cold cookies
directions: Cream the butter at medium speed.
Add both sugars.
Beat in egg, flour, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Roll in a ball.
Chill in refrigerator 3 hours or overnight.
Drop spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: stewed chicken casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in about 2 cups broth from chicken (cooked).
Cook noodles in salt water; drain and rinse.
Bone and dice cooked chicken.
Combine all ingredients into casserole. Cover and bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Add more broth if casserole becomes dry.

title: spiced cranberry tea
directions: Cook in 2 to 3 quarts water; strain and add 3 cups sugar. Keep refrigerated to thin and serve hot.
Makes 1 to 2 gallons tea.

title: ranch stew
directions: Saute peppers, onions and garlic in a small amount of margarine.
Add browned ground beef, chile tomatoes, stewed tomatoes, kidney beans, sugar and salt.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with Mexican corn bread or regular corn bread.

title: green bean and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and chop onion; season to taste.
Place in casserole dish.
On top of this, lay green beans (drained), then cover with Tater Tots.
Mix cream of chicken soup with milk.
Pour over all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs with milk; gradually beat in flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Beat until very smooth.
Holding the opening of a funnel closed, fill funnel with the batter.
Open the end of the funnel; let dough run out in a stream into deep, hot fat (375°). Move the funnel to make a pattern, starting at the center of the pan and swirling batter outward in a circle.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, or until golden brown.
When cakes are done, drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar and cinnamon.
Very delicious.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Make hole in center of mixture. Pour strawberries, oil and eggs in hole.
Mix by hand very well. Grease 2 loaf pans and flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Blend soft cream cheese and juice.
Spread on sliced cool bread. Freezes well.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pie shell until brown.
On stove, melt Hershey bars, marshmallows and milk.
After all melted, take off stove and let cool.
After cooled, stir in half of the Cool Whip, then put in pie crust.
Put rest of Cool Whip on top.

title: western dip
directions: Mix together.
Great with potato chips or vegetables.

title: honey spice bread
directions: Combine milk and brown sugar.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Blend in milk mixture, honey, eggs and oil.
Turn batter into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cover with foil for last 15 minutes.

title: oil pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt. Add oil.
Mix well. Sprinkle cold water over mixture. Stir in with fork.
The mixture will form into a ball. Divide into two balls, one ball a little larger to be the bottom crust.
Roll out between wax paper.
Recipe may be halved. Quick, good and easy.

title: 7 layer cookie
directions: Melt butter or margarine in pan.
Add cracker crumbs; mix well.
Spread crumbs in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan; pat firmly and evenly.
Spread chocolate chips, peanut butter or butterscotch chips over crumbs evenly.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over all.
Add coconut, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Don't let cookies cool for more than 1 1/2 hours before cutting.

title: buttermilk pie(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set out pie shell.
Place the softened butter in a large mixer bowl.
Add the sugar and cream well.
Add flour, eggs, buttermilk, lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Mix. Pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg lightly over the top. Bake for 1 hour or until the top is golden brown.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine crackers, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Put in a 9-inch cake pan. Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: fergosa (italian bread)
directions: Combine 1/2 cup cheese, Bisquick and milk. Beat until smooth; will be sticky. Knead 10 times on floured board, working in small amount of flour if too sticky. Butter 8 or 9-inch pie plate and also your hands. Spread in bottom of pie plate. Combine 1 cup of cheese and egg. Spread on crust. Spread on sauteed onion and top with poppy seeds. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Makes 6 slices.

title: nacho salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss everything together, except the salad dressing.
When ready to serve, mix in the salad dressing.

title: dipsy doodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add chopped tomatoes, soup, water and noodles.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cheese slices on top after mix is simmered.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Grease a shallow 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: inkokta rodbetor(pickled beets)
directions: Cut off all but 2-inches of beet tops.
Leave beets whole with root ends attached.
Heat water, vinegar and salt to boiling.
Add beets.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and cook until tender, 35 to 45 minutes. Drain.
Run cold water over beets. Slip off skins and remove root ends.
Cut beets into slices.
Place beets and onion in glass or plastic bowl.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 2 minutes.
Pour over beets and onion. Cover and refrigerate, spooning marinade over beets occasionally, at least 12 hours.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: spicy hermits
directions: Mix sugar, flour, spices, salt, soda and egg together.
Add shortening and water; mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Make 1-inch balls on cookie sheet; leave space between.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Pour into ice cream freezer and make according to manufacturer's directions.

title: coated nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place nuts on a cookie sheet in oven for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Put nuts in a strainer with large holes, like a French fry basket, and shake off the skins or take nuts outside and blow off the skins. Set aside.
Grease the 2 cookie sheets with margarine or butter. Cook sugar, water, cinnamon and salt to soft ball stage 236° without stirring.
Remove from heat; add the vanilla, then add nuts.
Stir quickly until all nuts are coated, then turn out on a greased cookie sheet.
Cool, then separate.

title: dessert cake
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan as directed.
Cool well.
Blend milk, cream cheese and pudding mix well.
Spread over cake. Sprinkle pineapple over all.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: baked s'mores
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Combine cookie mix, contents of buttery flavor packet from mix, egg and water in a large bowl.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Divide cookie dough in half.
Press half the dough evenly in pan.
Cut each chocolate bar into 12 sections and arrange into 4 rows with 9 sections in each row.
Place spoonfuls of Marshmallow Creme on top of chocolate.
Spread to cover.
Drop remaining cookie dough by teaspoonfuls on top of Creme.
Spread slightly with back of spoon. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely and cut into squares.
Makes 9 squares.

title: diabetic - sugarless apple pie
directions: Combine juice and cornstarch in small saucepan; thicken over low heat until clear.
Add margarine, cinnamon and Equal.
Mix with apples.
Place in prepared crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: famous barr french onion soup
directions: Slice onions thin.
Melt butter in large pot.
Saute onions in butter for 1 1/2 hours over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients except bouillon.
Saute for 10 minutes over low heat.
Add bouillon; simmer 2 hours.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fill soup bowls with soup.
Slice a piece of French bread and drop into each bowl.
Top with generous amount of grated Swiss cheese.
Place in broiler for about 5 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: pie crust
directions: Measure flour, salt and baking powder in bowl.
Cut in shortening to size of peas.
Get enough dough for one crust and place on floured cloth or board.
Roll out to fit pie pan and place in pan.
Repeat for top crust.

title: heavenly pie(lemon icebox meringue)
directions: Shell:
Sift 1 cup sugar and cream of tartar together.
Beat whites of eggs in stiff peaks, but not dry.
Slowly add sugar, beating constantly.
Spread meringue on bottom and side of well-greased pie pan.
Make bottom 1/4-inch thick, side thicker. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons coconut on top and bake at 275°.

title: apple oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin tins.
Soak oats in milk for 15 minutes.
Add egg, oil, molasses and apple.
Mix well. Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to oat mixture.
Stir until just combined.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.
Has 102 calories.

title: potato deluxe casserole
directions: Mix together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1 cup of crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese spritz cookies
directions: Cream cheese, sugar and margarine until fluffy. Add flour gradually until well blended. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until fluffy.
Add flour, a little at a time, and then the lemon extract.
Grease a tube pan with butter and dust with flour.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Very good.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Chop all vegetables into 1/2-inch pieces.
Remove as many of the hot pepper seeds as desired to determine how hot you want the salsa (the more seeds you leave in, the hotter the salsa).
Saute the vegetables in hot oil in skillet for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours, until at least half the liquid boils off.
Freezes well.
Use refrigerated salsa within 2 weeks.
A great way to use your garden produce!

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain very well.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls the size of large marbles.
Freeze on cookie sheets; remove and store in plastic bag in freezer.
To serve, bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned (7 to 10 minutes, if unfrozen).
Makes about 80.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes on top of stove and then put in oven with remaining ingredients for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles by directions on the package.
Drain.
Cook together hamburger and onion.
Turning meat with fork, add tomato paste and seasoning.
Add corn and cook 3 or 4 minutes.

title: easy dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling evenly in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over pie filling (do not stir).
Put butter in rows over entire cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread apples evenly in baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle with salt, cinnamon and water.
Mix flour, sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Spread crumb mixture over apples.
Bake uncovered about 40 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix flour, mayonnaise and enough milk to make paste.
Put into a greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil eggs. Break spaghetti into small pieces before boiling. Chop vegetables up fine. Sprinkle liberally with Johnny's Salad Elegance.
Mix in Zesty Italian dressing and toss.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Marinate the brisket in all the ingredients, except barbecue sauce, for 24 hours.
Remove the brisket from marinade and place in a baking dish and pour on the barbecue sauce.
Cover and bake at 300° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: red hot jello
directions: Dissolve red hots in boiling water. Add jello and applesauce. Chill and serve.

title: no bake haystack cookies
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a pan, bring to a boil and boil for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add last 4 ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: stuffed peppers(foil wrapped on open fire)
directions: Cut off the stem ends of the peppers; remove the seeds and discard.
Boil pepper shells for 5 minutes in lightly salted water; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and stuff peppers. Wrap in a double layer of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Bake in medium hot coals for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: graham streusel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix crumbs, nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter; set aside.
Blend mix, water, oil and eggs at low speed, about 30 seconds.
Then beat at medium speed for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the vanilla wafers and 1 stick butter or oleo and press in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Let set in freezer.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and molasses.
Sift together and stir in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.

title: quick chocolate truffles
directions: Roll vanilla wafers into crumbs and set aside.
Put Cool Whip into a large mixing bowl.
Melt chocolate bars in a double boiler and pour into bowl with Cool Whip.
Stir together.
Place in refrigerator for 5 minutes, then take spoonfuls and roll in crumbs.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat the shortening, sugar and peanut butter. Add eggs, water and vanilla until creamy. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate 1 hour. Roll in balls. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grandma dykun's fresh kosher pickles
directions: Boil water. Make brine with salt.
Peel garlic and put on bottom of jar with half dill.
Pack cucumbers in a jar.
Put in spices.
Add brine.
Put rest of dill on top.
Add heel of rye bread.
Fill to top with brine.
Cover.
Set at room temperature 1 week.
After that, refrigerate.

title: onion gravy
directions: Melt oleo; add flour and stir.
Add water and cook until thick.
Put a slice of onion on each burger.
Pour gravy over burgers.
Cover.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt together the chocolate and the margarine. Beat together the eggs and the sugar, then drizzle in the melted chocolate mixture.
Add the flour, baking powder and salt.
Refrigerate for at least 5 minutes. Roll into balls and roll in the confectioners sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: splendid spinach
directions: Boil water and sugar until caramelized about 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in almonds.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Break into pieces. Mix vinegar, oil, Tabasco, curry and brown sugar.
Toss spinach with fruit, dressing and almonds.
May substitute other fruits.

title: butterscotch crunches
directions: Melt
the
butterscotch
bits in double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir in a can of cocktail peanuts and chow mein noodles. Drop
by
spoonful	on
foil
covered cookie sheets. Place	in cool area or refrigerator until firm.
Makes a very large
batch. Takes
about
15 minutes to make.
You can very easily
cut
this recipe in half by simply using 1 package of bits,
etc.
Don't make them too large as they are very sweet and smaller looks neater for a party tray.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients except for the cheese and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until cheese is lightly browned.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook
noodles
like
on
box.
Brown
hamburger.
Add hamburger to sauce.
Dice
onion; add to sauce.
Put one layer of sauce in ovenproof
pan.
Put
one
layer of cheese and one layer of noodles.
Repeat each until all ingredients are used. Cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: delicious twinkie cake
directions: Pour 2 cups cold milk into bowl; add pudding mix.
Use electric mixer at low speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Place Twinkies on bottom of another flat bottom bowl.
Drain and add the juice from the pineapple.
Add pudding mix; next, add the crushed pineapple. Then add Cool Whip.
Let chill for 3 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate whipped cream pie(diabetic)
directions: Prepare vanilla wafer crust (reserving 2 tablespoons crumb mixture).
Pack into a 9-inch pie pan and chill in refrigerator at least 2 hours before making filling.
Prepare pudding according to package directions using the skim milk.
Allow it to cool for 1/2 hour.
Spoon pudding carefully into chilled pie shell and chill until pudding is firm.
Spread whipped topping gently across top of pie with a spatula.
Scatter the reserved crumbs on top.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick (when filling starts to bubble cook 3 minutes), stirring constantly, as it will stick.
Cool slightly and stir in vanilla.
Keep stirred.
Top with meringue.
The filling can be used as pudding.

title: quick vanilla ice cream
directions: Put everything in same bowl and beat well.
Freeze until firm.

title: honey chicken wings
directions: Mix and marinate overnight for best results.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: broiled asparagus
directions: Wash and trim ends of asparagus; put on cookie sheet. Spray with olive oil Pam, salt and pepper. Broil for about 15 minutes and serve.

title: courgettes with tomatoes and herbs
directions: Bring the Courgettes to the boil, in salted water, and cook for 3 minutes.
Drain and place in an ovenproof dish.
Heat butter; add tomatoes, garlic or onion, herbs and salt and cook until a thickish mixture forms.
Taste and adjust seasoning; spoon over Courgettes.
Sprinkle with cheese and breadcrumbs and bake at gas mark 4 (325°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot by itself, or with beefburgers, chops or steaks.

title: english muffin canapes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread on muffin halves and broil until bubbly.
Cut each muffin into 4 wedges.
Serve hot.

title: texas fudge cake
directions: Mix together flour,
salt
and	soda.
In
pot bring to boil 2 sticks
butter
or	margarine,
water and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Add all
at
once the cooked mixture to the flour mix; add eggs and
sour
cream and mix together.	Bake in a greased (no flour) 13 x
9-inch
pan
at
for
20 to 25 minutes. Frost while hot.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute pepper and onion in margarine. Add flour and stir in milk. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Continue to cook and stir until cheese melts. Pour in buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine
all ingredients, except butter, in a large pan or bowl.
Pour
into oven-safe dish.
Add butter or margarine cut into small squares on top and sprinkle with a little brown or white
sugar.
Bake
at 350° for 35 minutes.
You can serve it hot right
from
the oven or you can prepare the following sauce to serve over it.

title: cheese vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients into a crock pot and cook for 4 hours.

title: gloria's easy "light" cake
directions: Select your favorite
flavor cake mix.
Spray desired pan or pans with cooking spray.
Prepare according to package directions with the following modifications:
Add 1 tablespoon flour to dry mix and blend well.
Substitute an equal measure of unsweetened applesauce for vegetable oil and substitute equal number of egg whites for eggs.
Cool in pan on rack.
Remove when cool.
Frost or sprinkle powdered sugar.
Yields 16 servings.

title: plum pie
directions: In a small bowl, combine brown sugar and crumbs. Line a 9 inch pie pan with bottom crust; sprinkle with brown sugar mixture and pack gently. Cover with plums. Combine the sugar, flour and cinnamon; cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over plums. Roll out remaining pastry to fit top of pie. Make small cuts or slits in top crust; place over plums. Seal and flute edges. Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°; bake 25 minutes more or until golden brown.

title: veg-all corn bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting (leftover chopped, cooked ham or sausage can be added; 1/2 package Mexican corn bread mix and 1/2 regular corn bread mix make a flavorable taste).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Crush Oreos very fine.
Mix together well Oreos, Cool Whip and ice cream which has been slightly softened.
For a more chocolate flavor, add cocoa to taste.
Pour into 8 1/2 x 13-inch dish and freeze.

title: hot relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer covered on low 1 to 1 1/2 hours or pressure cook on medium to low for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: pioneer pancakes
directions: Pour boiling water over cornmeal and molasses; let stand for 5 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients with a rotary beater until it is smooth; stir in cornmeal mixture.
Pour the batter from a 1/4-cup measuring cup onto the hot griddle.
(Grease griddle, if necessary.)
Bake until bubbles appear.
Turn and bake the other side until golden brown.
Makes about 18.

title: black raspberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Spray bottom and sides of a 10-inch tube or spring form pan with cooking spray. In a large bowl, combine flour and 3/4 cup sugar. Using a pastry blender or fork, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture. To remaining crumb mixture, add baking powder, baking soda, salt, sour cream, almond extract and 1 egg. Blend well. Spread dough over bottom and 1 inch up sides of prepared pan. Pat dough about 1/4 inch thick on sides.

title: imperial torte
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Blend oleo and sugar first.
Add vanilla.
Add one egg at a time.
Mix in the cake flour.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° until done.
Torte is done when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: bible cake(this cake is filled with sweet goodies.)
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
In a separate dish, sift flour, baking powder and salt. Mix in first mixture, alternating with milk.
Stir in honey, add spices and mix until well blended.
Add raisins, figs and almonds. Beat well, then pour batter into a well-greased loaf pan and bake in a 325° oven for 50 minutes.
Let cake cool, then slice.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onions until tender.
Place broccoli and onions in casserole dish after draining.
Melt butter in saucepan. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and stir until slightly thickened.
Add cream cheese.
Blend until bubbles.
Pour over broccoli and mix.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
This is made in the saucepan, beating with a spoon.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli slightly.
Put broccoli in a greased casserole dish.
Top with chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together.
Pour on top of chicken, making sure some gets down to the broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and add bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caldo verde(kale soup)
directions: Saute onion with oil.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook until soft.
Mash them into the water.
Slice kale as thinly as possible.
Add to potatoes.
Simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.
Add onion.
Heat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Serve with cornbread.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Melt margarine in pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in a baking dish or pan.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: super salad
directions: Tear and line salad bowl with lettuce.
Build salad in layers: lettuce, onions, celery, bell pepper, peas, chestnuts.
Cover entire salad with mayonnaise followed with thick layer of grated Parmesan cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: simple potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (salt and pepper may be added).

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
Add soda to buttermilk and combine with yeast water.
Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients.
Store in refrigerator in covered container.
Cut as desired.
Let rise at least 30 minutes. Bake at 425° until lightly browned.

title: my best gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add beaten egg.
Measure and sift dry ingredients.
Mix molasses with hot water, add dry ingredients alternately with liquid, a little at a time;
beat after each addition.
Bake in a paper-lined pan (9 x 9 x 2) in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 15 squares.

title: carolers' chocolate coffee
directions: *Semi-sweet chocolate may be substituted if you prefer the taste.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make 2 round loaves.
Wrap in foil. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Punch holes in top and bottom of foil. Place on broil pan to allow excess grease to drip off.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mrs. scott's crisp green tomato pickles
directions: Tie several small bags of cloves, allspice, mace, cinnamon and ginger.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove to paper towel to drain. Saut onion in drippings until tender. Add broth, water and potatoes; then bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add salt and pepper; mix well. Add corn and 3/4 of the milk. Combine flour and remaining milk and mix until smooth. Add to mixture. Bring to a boil to cook and stir for 2 minutes. Garnish with bacon and parsley. Yield: 6 servings.

title: wild strawberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Bring juice to a boil.
Remove from heat and add jello.
When this starts to congeal, add cottage cheese, whipped topping and pecans.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt.
Dip balls into chocolate and set on waxed paper to dry.

title: orange date loaf
directions: Mix
soda in buttermilk.
Stir Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs
and	orange rind.
Alternate flour and buttermilk.
Stir in	dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: breakfast strata
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in glass casserole dish and refrigerate overnight, covered.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, uncovered.
Serve warm.
You may add any of the following:
green peppers, onions, ham.
Serve with fruit.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Make jello except add 3/4 cup boiling water and 3/4 cup cold water.
Let jello slightly gel, then add the crushed pineapples and cranberries and stir well.
Chop nuts and place on top. Chill. Can split recipe.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips in the microwave until creamy.
Stir.
Pour over cereal and mix well. Put sugar in a bag and add cereal mixture.
Shake well to coat. Use 2 cookie sheets to cool.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons shortening in skillet.
Salt and pepper chops; flour.
Brown on both sides.
Saute onions until clear looking.
In 2-quart casserole, layer potatoes, onions, potatoes and onions.
Place chops on top.
Pour soup over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: nee nee's two fruits, two vegetables salad
directions: Slice grapes in half.
Cut apples and tomatoes in thin 1-inch pieces.
Mix all ingredients together at least a half hour before serving.

title: spicy chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender, reserving broth.
Cool, then remove from bone.
Shred and set aside.

title: homemade pasta
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, mix ingredients.
Knead dough ball for 10 minutes, adding a few drops of water if dough seems too dry or a little flour if too sticky.
Place dough ball in a plastic bag and put in refrigerator for 1 hour to relax the gluten.
Cut the ball into 4 parts.
With a floured rolling pin or pasta machine, roll dough and cut as desired.

title: mr. d's delicious doughnuts
directions: Separate biscuits and poke a hole in middle, spreading biscuit with thumbs.
Put in pan of hot oil.
Turn it over when brown. Remove when golden brown.
Shake in a bag of sugar mixture or powdered sugar.

title: chicken or turkey divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until slightly tender and cool.
Put in bottom of baking dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch).
Cover with chicken or turkey.
Top with cheese slices; cover with mixture of soup and evaporated milk or sour cream.
Bake for 25 minutes, uncovered.
Top with onion rings; bake another 5 or 10 minutes.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook onions and parsley in butter for 5 minutes.
Add carrots, consomme, sugar and nutmeg.
Cover; cook for 15 minutes.
Uncover; cook 15 minutes longer, or until carrots are tender and sauce is slightly thick.

title: easy sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles and if they were too salty, rinse and drain again.
Cut into chunks and put into a clean quart jar.
(Throw out dill stalks.)
Pour sugar over pickles in jar.
Cover and refrigerate for a few days until sugar is liquid.
Shake jar occasionally to blend in sugar.

title: diabetic date nut cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sweetener and vanilla, which have been beaten together.
Add eggs and applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Beat until well blended. Turn into a buttered loaf or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafer crumbs, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and melted butter or margarine well.
Make into small balls.
In a double boiler, melt wax and chocolate bits.
Dip balls in chocolate with fork.
Lift out and put on wax paper or foil to set.

title: holiday poke cake
directions: Prepare, bake and cool cake according to directions for 2 9 inch layers.
Place players, top sides up in 2 clean player pans. Pierce cakes with large fork at 1/2 inch intervals.
Stir 1 c. boiling water into each flavor jello in seperate bowls.
Stir 2 minutes, until dissolved.
Carefully pour red gelatin over one cake layer and green over the other.
Refrigerate 3 hours before removing from pans and serving.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken and shred.
Put in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour soup on top.
Put desired amount grated cheese on top.
Prepare Stove Top dressing.
Spread over chicken dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender and drain. Cook chicken until done, I usually boil it. Melt butter, add onion, cook until tender. Add cheese and melt. Add can of cream of chicken, mix well. Add salt, pepper, and garlic to spaghetti. Add chicken and cheese mixture, you can add milk if too thick.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Combine
all
ingredients in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, stirring well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and
minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Serves 8.

title: canned fruit salad
directions: Mix all together (juice and all).
It is best if left to stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Prepare the day before serving.
Peel and slice onions, cut slices in half.
Slice mushrooms.
Saute onions and mushrooms in small amount of vegetable oil or margarine.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish layer onions and mushrooms.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Melt margarine and mix with crumbled buns.
Pour bread crumbs on cheese.
Mix together soup, milk, salt, pepper and soy sauce. Pour over onion mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Cover apples with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 hours until they are the consistency of applesauce or apple butter.
They will be dark brown.
Cool.
Then add sugar, flour, lemon extract and cinnamon and stir well.

title: tex-mex dip(light)
directions: Mash, peel and pit avocados.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning in separate bowl. Spread refried beans on a large shallow serving platter.
Top with seasoned avocado mixture.
Layer sour cream taco mixture.
Sprinkle with onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with cheese.
Serve chilled or at room temperature with lo-fat tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together brown sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add pumpkin and milk; mix well.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, ginger, baking soda and cloves; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan; cool.
Wrap and store overnight before slicing. Makes 1 loaf.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Stirring, simmer for 1minute.
Add milk, half and half and crushed bouillon.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add crabmeat.
Simmer long enough to heat crabmeat through.
Add Old Bay to taste.

title: spinach and cheese pie
directions: Hollow out the centers and saute with the traditional chopped celery, bell pepper and onion in margarine.
(The mirlitons must be cut in half and boiled in water about 20 to 30 minutes until tender.)

title: "proposal" cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pat in cake pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over cooled crust.
Beat pudding with milk. Spread over cream cheese layer. Beat pudding with milk.
Spread over first pudding layer. Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: honey chicken
directions: Heat all together and add chicken. Cook until done. May prepare on stove top in covered skillet or in 350° oven.

title: potato pork casserole
directions: Using a 9 x 13 pan start layering with the potatoes; season as you go along. After you finish layering the potatoes, meat and onions, mix the soups and can of water together and pour over the casserole. If you wish, you can top with crumbled potato chips or crackers. Bake at 350° until potatoes and meat are done. *Ground beef can be substituted for pork chops.

title: your mother's chalah(at least four generations)
directions: Combine oil, salt and sugar.
Add boiling water and cold water.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add eggs and yeast to water.
Add oil mixture.
Work in about 8 cups of flour (maybe a little less) and knead until smooth.
Let rise for 1 to 2 hours.

title: swiss egg bread - challah braid
directions: In a saucepan heat milk.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and 1/4 cup margarine.
Stir until margarine melts.
In a large bowl sprinkle yeast over 1/4 cup warm water.
Stir until yeast is dissolved.
Stir in milk mixture and add eggs, one at a time.

title: appetizer spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls and bake immediately, using cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: mary's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a blender.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda. Pour over popped corn (2 cups unpopped corn).
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring frequently.

title: peach pie filling
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except Miracle Whip.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Cool and add Miracle Whip salad dressing.

title: angel food bliss cake
directions: Cut cake horizontally to make 2 layers. Mix frosting, cinnamon, cocoa and vanilla, stirring well. Frost cake layers. Before serving, pour apple pie filling in center of cake.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: bird's nest pudding
directions: Pare and core apples.
Place upright in buttered baking dish. Fill holes in apples with the raisins.
Mix eggs, sugar, salt and milk and pour over apples.
Bake in 325° oven until apples are tender and custard looks curdled, about 70 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat on medium speed until creamy.
Add egg, combine rest of ingredients. Drop by tablespoons onto an ungreased baking sheet 3 inches apart. Bake 8 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: tortilla soup
directions: *May use 1/2 can Ro-Tel and one 16 ounce can stewed tomatoes, chopped.

title: shrimp cocktail delight
directions: Spread cream cheese on plate.
Pour cocktail sauce over cheese.
Spread 1 can shrimp (drained) over cream cheese and cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: yummy chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: bread puddin'
directions: Cut
bread in 1-inch squares;
place in lightly greased 1 3/4 x 7 1/2
x	1
3/4-inch dish.
Slightly beat 3 eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Heat milk slowly, add to
egg mixture,
pour
over
bread
and
sprinkle
cinnamon. Combine cheese and 1/2
cup
sugar and blend well.	Add 1 egg. Spread over bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: cranberry chunk salad - frozen
directions: Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Add pineapple, walnuts and bananas.
Fold in cream and cranberry sauce.
Turn into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and cheese until fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each. Stir in flour.
Pour in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jalapeno cheese roll
directions: Mix Velveeta and jalapeno cheese thoroughly.
Roll out thin on a flat surface covered with waxed paper.
Mix cream cheese, bell pepper, jalapeno pepper, green onions, and nuts.
Pat or roll out onto first layer of cheese.
Roll up into log.
Cut into small logs and wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill, slice and serve on crackers. Refrigerates well and can be frozen.

title: cherry punch
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young and take only such as have been reared in good moral atmosphere.
Some insist in keeping them in a pickle.
Others are constantly getting them in hot water.
This only makes them more sour, hard and bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses to taste.
Then wrap them well in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line pan with Pam or paper.
Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon.
Pour into sheet cake pan.
Spread dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture; sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix and nuts.
Bake for 60 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, orange juice, sugar and cornstarch; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in liqueur, vanilla and lemon peel.
Cover surface with plastic wrap and chill.

title: creamy hot beef dip
directions: Combine first eight ingredients in a 1-quart baking dish. Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.
Yield: about 2 cups.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Using a double boiler, mix flour, sugar and salt.
Scald milk in microwave and pour it over flour mixture, stirring constantly. Add milk mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Add to milk mixture when it thickens, stirring well.

title: taffy
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients together until a hard ball stage (263°).
Remove from the fire.
Add the butter and flavoring and pour into a greased pan.
When cool enough to handle comfortably, pull the mixture until rather firm.
Stretch out in a long rope and cut into pieces.
This is an old recipe.

title: ritz pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and remaining ingredients.
Pour in pie plate.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip.
Grate chocolate over all.
Grease pie plate generously. Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spanish meatballs
directions: Mix together; form into balls.
Roll in flour and fry until brown.
Add 1 can tomato soup.
Cook slow for several hours.

title: french silk pie
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan combine the 1 cup whipping cream, chocolate pieces, butter, and sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, till chocolate is melted.
This should take about 10 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Gradually stir about half of the hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks.
Return egg mixture to saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, till mixture is slightly thickened and nearly bubbly, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat (mixture may appear to separate).
Stir in creme de cacao or whipping cream.
Place saucepan in a bowl of ice water; stir occasionally till mixture stiffens and becomes hard to stir (20 minutes).

title: oatmeal apple raisin muffins
directions: Beat egg and stir in remaining ingredients just to moisten. Pour into 12 paper-lined muffin tins (1 tablespoon each).
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dip for strawberries
directions: Cream together until well blended.
Serve with strawberries.

title: likker pudding(very good with turkey and pork)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Pour milk in a quart casserole.
Grate coarsely sweet potatoes and put them into the milk as you grate. This will prevent them from turning dark.
Beat eggs well, adding sugar gradually.
Add cinnamon and almonds.
Mix thoroughly with the sweet potatoes.
Dot generously with butter.
Bake in a 300° oven about 1 1/2 hours or until the potatoes are cooked and bubbly.
Remove the casserole from the oven and pour bourbon over the top of the sweet potatoes.
This freezes well.
Serves 12.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream the butter and peanut butter; add vanilla and sugar gradually.
Form into small balls and set on wax paper.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix with mixer until crumbly.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Melt 12 ounces chocolate chips with 1/3 stick paraffin.
Heat in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture using fork.
Place on waxed paper.
Freeze or chill overnight.

title: mama lizzie's sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and flavor.
Stir well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Press with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in 350° oven until light golden brown.

title: best bar-b-que sauce
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, heat oil or spray with Pam until hot. Add onion and cook about 10 minutes until tender. Add other ingredients.
Heat to boiling over high heat.
Reduce heat to med-low and cook uncovered 45 minutes or until sauce thickens slightly.
If not using sauce right away, cover and refrigerate for up to 2 weeks.	Reserve 1 1/2 cups sauce to serve with chicken.
Generously brush meat with remaining sauce.
If grilling, turn meat and brush with sauce frequently.
Serves 12.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, corn syrup, sugar, vanilla, salt and margarine. Stir in pecans.
Pour in ungreased (baked) pastry shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes, then lower heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Filling should be set slightly less in center than around edge.

title: nanny's rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crabbies
directions: Let butter and cheeses soften to room temperature.
Mix together with mayonnaise and salts.
Add crabmeat and mix well. Spread on split muffins that have been slightly toasted (light brown).
Cut into fourths or sixths.
Store in freezer until ready to bake with wax paper between layers in bags or Tupperware.
When ready to serve, broil until bubbly and crisp, about 8 to 10 minutes or bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch carefully.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Slice bread in half.
Coat with butter.
Sprinkle cheese, garlic powder and parsley.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken breast special
directions: Cover chicken in water and boil until done.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the broth.
Mix together the soups and Ro-Tel.
Line a pan with Tostitos chips.
Put in chicken breasts, cut into small pieces. Pour soup/Ro-Tel mixture over chicken.
Cover with grated cheese and bake about 30 minutes at 400°.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put layer of cake in a pan, then a layer of Butterfinger.
Top with mixed mixture.
Repeat layers, topping with Butterfinger sprinkled on top.

title: golden wedding anniversary punch
directions: Cheese and ham just one piece in each one put the top on. Cook it in our new oven.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Combine first 5 items.
Stir in carrots, raisins, coconuts, nuts and pineapple.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla. Stir into flour mixture until batter is mixed; don't overstir. Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tortilla chicken hot dish
directions: Stir together soups, milk, onion and chilies. Stir in chicken and broth. Grease casserole dish and spread half the tortillas in bottom. Spread half the chicken mixture over the tortillas, then half the cheese. Repeat. Refrigerate for 24 hours and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serves 6.

title: clam pie hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix together and put into a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix together baking powder, flour and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. When cool, cut into squares.

title: whole wheat banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine bananas and buttermilk or yogurt, stirring just enough to mix.
Add dry ingredients alternately with banana mixture.
Stir in nuts; pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb royal salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until tender 10 minutes.
Dissolve jello in mixture.
Let set until cool and thickened.
Add celery and nuts.
Chill.

title: coffee candy bar shake
directions: Make coffee; chill and set aside.

title: mother's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cukes in thin rings; do not pare.
Cut peppers in thin strips.
Cut onion in thin rings.
Dissolve salt in ice water and place over vegetables.
Let stand 3 hours and drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices and bring to boil.
Add drained vegetables and heat to boiling point.
Do not boil.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: freezing corn
directions: Clean corn.
Cut off cob (raw).
Mix all ingredients together and cook until almost done.
Cool and freeze.

title: baker's icing
directions: Mix flour and milk until smooth.
Cook slowly until thick (medium-high heat).
Remove from heat and refrigerate until cool. Mix cold mixture with margarine and Crisco.
Blend altogether at low speed and add salt.
Beat at high speed until smooth and fluffy.
Blend in sugar (high speed) 1/4 at a time.
Add vanilla and beat 1 minute at high speed.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave 3 to 5 minutes or until chips melt.
Stir, pour in pan and refrigerate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir and mix well.
Cover.
Chill until ready to be used.
Yields approximately 3 cups.

title: noodle pie
directions: Break up noodles and boil in salted water.
Drain and toss with oleo.
Beat eggs.
Add ricotta cheese, eggs, sugar and flavoring.
Add milk and noodles.
Combine all.
Butter 9x13 pan. Pour in and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven when edges are brown and leave pan in oven for 5 mins.

title: chinese chocolettes
directions: Melt chocolate morsels over hot water in double boiler.
Stir in condensed milk.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add noodles (chow mein), nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator in hot weather.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: raspberry jello
directions: Mix jello with boiling water; add raspberries.
Add applesauce.
Mix well.
Allow to set in refrigerator.
Remove and place marshmallows on top and then top with sour cream.

title: toffee bars
directions: At least 3 days before serving, beat together flour, 1 cup sugar, butter (softened), vanilla and egg yolk. Press batter into a greased 10 x 15-inch baking sheet. Beat the egg white and brush over the batter. Sprinkle with sugar and chopped pecans. Bake at 275° for 3/4 to 1 hour. If bars don't look sugared, lightly sugar again. Cut into bars while hot. Store tightly covered.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and melted butter into 9 x 13 pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool. Mix cream cheese, whipped topping and powdered sugar. Spread on pretzel layer. Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water. Add frozen strawberries, then crushed pineapple (optional). When partially set, pour on top of other 2 layers. Refrigerate.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Combine water, salt and rice; cook 12 minutes.
Add soup mix; cook 3 minutes.
Do not drain.
While rice, etc., are cooking, cook sausage until well done; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and put into casserole.
Cover with foil and bake in a 250° oven for 2 hours.

title: meat manicotti
directions: Use an 8 or 9 x 4-inch casserole.
Cook manicotti as directed. Saute hamburg in olive oil until brown.
Mix thoroughly with egg, cheese, bread crumbs, parsley and seasonings.
Stuff manicotti. Cover bottom of casserole with spaghetti sauce, then arrange manicotti over sauce and cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rudy's farm sausage swirls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent rolls into rectangles. Spread with a thin layer of uncooked sausage.
Top each rectangle with either cheese or mustard (about 2 tablespoons).
Roll (from short end).
Chill until firm.
Thinly slice each roll (10 slices). Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm or hot.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: In small saucepan, stir together sugar, cornstarch, salt and orange peel.
Slowly stir orange juice into mixture.
Add butter. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Cover; bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, diced onions, brown sugar and syrup together. After mixing, lay 3 slices of bacon on beans and bake at 400° for 1 hour, depending on oven temperatures.
May need to bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Will serve approximately 12 people.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Put Cheese Nips on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: key west chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except lettuce and pita bread; cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Spoon chicken mixture into pita halves.
Garnish with lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix well and pour in buttered square pan.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients and stir until mixed; do not beat.
Bake in a greased and floured 10 in tube pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: mom's cranapple dish
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in greased dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and press on top of fruit mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lamb meat loaf
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine lamb and hamburger meat.
Add 2 eggs, V-8 juice and crumbled brown bread.
Mix items together. Add seasonings to include dry mustard, garlic salt, black pepper, cumin, thyme and basil.
Combine all meat and seasonings; add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Form into a meat loaf; cover top with tomato sauce.
Place in oven at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Measure peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme into a bowl and set aside.
Put remaining 3 ingredients into a 2-quart saucepan and cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Boil until mixture reaches 238° on a candy thermometer or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir quickly (2 to 3 minutes) and pour into buttered dish.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix together and shape into small balls.
Brown and drain well.

title: frozen margaritas
directions: Rub rim of glass with lime and dip in Margarita salt.
Put frozen limeade, tequila and Triple Sec in blender and add ice until about 3/4 full.
Blend.
Yields 14 ounces.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In Presto cooker, add shortening and heat.
Lightly brown celery and onion.
Add salt, chili powder, tomato juice, vinegar, sugar, shrimp and rice.
Mix well.
Pressure 2 to 3 minutes with pressure regulator rocking slowly.
Cool cooker at once by running water over cooker in sink.
Serve at once.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: mexican ranch eggs
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart pan over low heat.
Add chopped onions.
Saute 3 to 4 minutes over moderate heat.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer uncovered about 20 minutes; stir occasionally.
Cook rice according to package directions.
When sauce and rice are ready, poach eggs until all whites
are cooked but
yolks are soft.
In each of 2 small au gratin dishes, spoon 1/2 cup to 1 cup of rice. Add 1/2 cup to 1 cup of sauce to each.
Place 2 eggs in each dish. Top with shredded cheese.
Melt cheese, as in a small electric toaster oven
on broil, but do not cook eggs further.
Pass salsa for topping.
Yield 2 servings.
There will be excess sauce which will refrigerate.

title: chess cake
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and one egg; mix
well and pat out in greased pan. Combine powdered sugar, 2
eggs
and cream cheese; mix
well
and
pour
over top of
first
layer.
Add chocolate chip morsels of desired flavor.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: baked ham and cheese spread
directions: Cut the top out of the bread and cut or pull out the insides leaving about 1/2 inch thick wall.
Combine remaining ingredients except paprika and fill loaf of bread.
Put into 250 oven for about 1 hour.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve warm with the bread cubes and/or crackers.

title: frozen pineapple-cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into an 8-inch square pan. Freeze several hours or overnight.
To serve, cut in squares and arrange on lettuce leaf.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop chipped dried beef and green onions in a blender.
Soften cream cheese.
Combine all ingredients until mixed.
Form into a ball.
Roll in nuts.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
Serve with Melba toast or crackers of your choice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dietetic oatmeal cookies(tripled)
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes at high speed.
Next put the next 5 ingredients in and beat at low speed, about 2 minutes.
Stir in oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: wampus bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in onions, potatoes and milk.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil (375°).
Cook until golden (3 to 5 minutes), turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: meringue
directions: Beat sugar into egg whites slowly and add cream of tartar. Beat until dry-light as cotton.
Add cornstarch and 1 cup sugar. Drop 2 tablespoons on brown paper for each meringue.
For a cap to cut off, swirl up.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix flour, pecans and margarine.
Mash into pie pan (sprayed with Pam) and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix 1 cup blueberries, 1/2 cup water and 3/4 cup sugar; boil for 1 minute.
Mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup water; add to boiling mixture and cook until fixed. Add 3 cups blueberries.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate. Yummy.
Must be made with fresh blueberries.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Roll graham crackers very fine.
Put marshmallows in about 1/4 cup sweet milk and melt on very low heat.
Cut everything else. Mix well and place in container lined with waxed paper. Refrigerate and slice as needed.
(I use 1/2 pound each of candied cherries and pineapple.)
I use a loaf pan to form the cake and then cut it into longways.
This will make two loaf pans.

title: roast beef
directions: Rub the outside of the roast with seasonings.
Do not rub into ends.
Melt shortening in Dutch oven.
Brown roast on all sides; drain fat.
Pour water over roast.
Add bouillon (or 1 cube). Cover; bake until tender at 325° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Remove roast; cut into thin slices or chill, then slice.
Heat in gravy made from drippings.

title: creamy cucumber spread
directions: Cream Miracle Whip and cream cheese until blended well.
Peel cucumber and slice lengthwise into quarters.
Cut out seeds. Finely dice.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Serve on cocktail rye bread.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Chop cabbage; boil until tender.
Drain.
Cook noodles; drain. Render the salt pork and onion until light tan.
Mix all ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: my pie crust
directions: Dissolve salt in cold water and sprinkle over flour and shortening. Blend flour, water and shortening.
Mix well and roll out.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine the cocoa, brown sugar and coffee in large mug and mix.
Add 1/4 cup of hot milk and stir; top with marshmallows.

title: radish salad
directions: Wash radishes and slice thinly.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cucumber chips
directions: Peel cucumbers if you prefer.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices. Place in colander in sink and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain well and place in medium bowl with green pepper and onion.

title: coffee and cream cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add 3/4 cup boiling water and vanilla.
Sift and add:
cake flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, salt, soda and 1 3/4 teaspoons instant coffee.
Add melted chocolate.
Beat egg whites and add 1/4 cup sugar and fold into coffee mixture.
Bake in 2 layers at 350° about 20 minutes.
