Whip whipping cream and flavor with 3/4 teaspoon instant coffee and 1/4 cup sugar.

title: chickpeas and macaroni
directions: Saute onion (cut in slivers) in olive oil.
Add tomato sauce and chickpeas.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook linguine and drain. Spoon chickpeas and sauce onto linguine.
Add Parmesan cheese. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: crab and cucumber mold
directions: In small saucepan, combine vinegar, lemon juice and 1/4 cup cold water.
Sprinkle gelatin over surface; let stand 5 minutes to soften.

title: classic green beans
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions; drain.
In 1-quart casserole, combine mushroom soup and milk.
Stir in beans and mushrooms.
Cook, uncovered, on High 4 to 6 minutes or until bubbly, stirring once.
Sprinkle with onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Lasts for a week or more.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Combine flour and whole wheat flour.
Combine brown sugar, yeast and salt with half of flour mixture; reserve remainder. Combine 2% milk, water and margarine in saucepan.
Heat to 130°. Add to yeast mixture; combine.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add half of reserved flour mixture; beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make moderately stiff dough.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double in bulk. Stir down; pour into well-greased casserole(s) or loaf pan(s). Cover; let rise until double in bulk.
Bake casseroles at 375° or loaf pans at 400° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: taffy dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and brown sugar together until very smooth.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Chill and serve with sliced apples.
Very delicious dessert.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Save juice off vegetables in case you want to thin stew.

title: little big orange cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add the egg and the remaining ingredients.
Drop by the spoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Set aside to cool.
Add Cool Whip and serve with fresh fruit.

title: cole slaw
directions: Boil first four ingredients together. Cool slightly and pour over cabbage.
Dressing will keep at least 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar (white), water, salt, sugar, cinnamon, cloves and pickling spice and bring to a boil.
Add beets and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cool until lukewarm.
Place all ingredients to sterilized canning jars and seal.
Let cool; place in a dark cool place.
Makes about 3 to 4 pints.

title: beef and red noodles
directions: Roll meat
cubes
in
seasoned flour; brown in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add
seasonings, puree and water.
Cover; simmer until meat is tender (about 1 hour).
Add noodles (more water may be
needed to keep noodles covered with sauce).
Cook for about 20
minutes, or until noodles are almost done, stirring once or twice.
Add peas; cook a few minutes longer.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook vermicelli and rinse in cold water; drain.
Marinate with Accent, lime juice and oil overnight.
Early next day, add other ingredients.
Sprinkle with spices and mix.
Refrigerate.
This salad keeps well.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Cook chicken until tender and cut into cubes.
Mix with dressing.

title: spicy goulash
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Cook hamburg.
Combine tomatoes, soup and mushrooms. Salt and pepper with macaroni and hamburg. Put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry glazed ham
directions: Take bone in ham with rind trimmed off and cut and score, fat side up.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain large can of whole sliced pineapple.

title: cherry surprize
directions: Cut angel food cake into cubes. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together until well blended. Add one carton of Cool Whip. Add the angel food cake cubes and mix thoroughly. Put in 9 x 13 cake pan. Top with cherry/blueberry pie filling. Refrigerate.

title: fruit bars
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, eggs, flour and flavoring.
Spoon over fruit.
Grease a pan with butter.
Place nuts in bottom.
Layer in cherries, pineapple and dates.
Cook 1 hour at 300° (maybe less). Use a large biscuit pan.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Tear lettuce into large pieces and place in bowl.
Dice bacon and fry until crisp.
Sprinkle over lettuce.
Melt butter with bacon fat.
Stir in cream and bring to a boil and simmer.
Beat eggs with salt, sugar, vinegar and pepper.
Pour into cream mixture and cook until thick.
Pour over lettuce and bacon; toss. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: artichoke tomato sauce for pasta
directions: Brown garlic
in
oil.	Drain marinade from artichokes. Add other ingredients
and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over your favorite pasta and top with freshly grated Parmesan.

title: cream of cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage; cut in wedges in salted water.
Only cook until half done.
Drain.
Put 1/2 of cabbage and 1/2 of margarine in a pan.
Sprinkle cheese over cabbage.
Crumble saltines; make 4 cups of White Sauce and pour half over casserole.
Repeat layers until you end with cheese and sauce.
Bake in a 400° oven until very bubbly.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Prepare pie crust by combining Oreo cookies and butter.
Press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Refrigerate.
In the top of a double boiler, melt Hershey Bar.
Add water, instant coffee and Kahlua.
Blend well.
Immediately fold melted chocolate mixture into Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: meatballs and marinara sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl (with spoon or by hand). Form into 1-inch meatballs.

title: baked ziti casserole
directions: Brown beef with oil, onion, garlic and parsley.
Add tomato paste and then add water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for approximately 1 hour.

title: family meat loaf ring(cooking time:  12 to 14 minutes)
directions: Combine brown sugar, tomato sauce and mustard.
Set aside. Combine beef, onion, cracker crumbs, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce mixture and stir until well mixed. Place mixture in 6 cup microproof ring mold.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over meat.
Cook on High for 12 to 14 minutes or until done.
Serves 6.

title: ice cream i
directions: Mix all together and freeze immediately.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; surround meat loaf with potatoes and carrots.
Pour can of tomato soup over meat loaf.
Cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes and carrots are done.

title: cheese popovers
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Add flour, salt and Cheddar cheese. Stir until ingredients are combined.
Pour into well-greased muffin cups.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes or until done.
Makes 9 popovers.

title: turnip greens with dumplings
directions: Wash greens, place in pot with seasonings and water.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook 30 minutes or until tender.

title: prune bread
directions: In a small bowl beat soda into buttermilk.
Let stand while mixing with electric beater; sugar, oil, eggs and prunes; sift flour, salt and cinnamon together.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes, then at 325° for another 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in container.
When ready to serve, place 1/4 cup of mix into cup and add boiling water.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with corn flakes; drizzle with melted butter.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
An excellent buffet or brunch dish.

title: "charmed" banana carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° Coat a 9 x 13 baking pan with nonstick spray; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.

title: crock-pot ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, onion and ham in crock-pot.
Top with mushroom soup, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook for 8 hours in crock-pot on low.

title: frosting
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Spread on cool cake.
Sets slowly.
You can set it in your refrigerator to rush it, if desired.

title: brown hamburger stew
directions: Mix meat with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil, stirring as needed. Drain off fat.
Add water and carrots.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add other sliced ingredients and simmer until tender (about 10 minutes).
Add tomato juice, heat and serve. Makes about six servings.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
Pour into crust.
Chill.

title: special  tea
directions: In bowl combine all ingredients, transfer to airtight container.
Use 2 or 3
teaspoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, shortening and buttermilk.
Set aside.
Combine the following dry ingredients: flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger.
Combine wet and dry ingredients; mix real good.
Batter should be sticky consistency.
Refrigerate to make batter easier to work with.

title: barbara bass casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in greased pan.
Place chicken on top of vegetables.
Pour soups over chicken; top with onion rings and Cheddar cheese.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, vanilla, water and shortening.
Stir with spoon until mixed well.
Stir in pecans.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll each in powdered sugar.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Cookies will be very soft when removed from oven.) Cool on a wire rack.
Yields 5 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken long rice
directions: Heat oil in a large pot.
Add garlic and saute until light brown.
Add chicken and saute until brown.
Add broth (or water) and fresh ginger.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer for 40 minutes.
Shred chicken, return to broth and add long rice, cooking another 5-10 minutes until long rice is clear in color. Add mushrooms and turn off heat.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Top off with chopped green onions

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put
flour,
sugar,
salt, soda, baking powder and caraway seed in a mixing bowl and stir well. Add raisins, then add
egg and shortening and stir.
Gradually add buttermilk until a firm,
but
not	stiff
dough is formed (like biscuit dough).

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Brown ribs in hot frypan and season with salt and pepper and dash of garlic powder.
After browning ribs, saute onions in drippings.
Place a layer of kraut in bottom of casserole, layer of ribs and some of the sauteed onion.
Continue layering of ribs and kraut until finished.
Bake in slow oven for 1 to 2 hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco; add eggs and mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Roll into balls about the size of a walnut; flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Spray pan.
Use 9 x 12-inch pan or two pie pans or favorite cornbread pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 12 or more.
Heats over should there be leftovers.
Also freezes well.

title: diabetic banana nut bread
directions: Sprinkle artificial sweetener over bananas and mix well. Blend in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add walnuts.
Blend thoroughly into banana mixture, but do not overmix.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. Serves 12.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring fruit cocktail to a boil.
Add jello and mix well. Cool.
In blender put 2 envelopes Dream Whip, milk as directed on package and softened cream cheese.
Blend well.
Fold into jello and mix well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch lightly greased dish.
Chill until firm.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Mix well; add milk, then coconut.
Bake in unbaked pie shell in slow oven at 350° until firm in center.

title: carol's hot fudge cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together. Set aside.
In saucepan, add Crisco, margarine, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over the sugar and flour mixture.
Mix vanilla, soda, buttermilk and cinnamon together.
Add to beaten eggs and put in with the mixture, mixing well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Frost with Hot Fudge Icing.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Line the bottom of a large serving bowl with tomato slices.
In a separate bowl, combine onion, basil and 1 teaspoon of the salt. Sprinkle some of the onion mixture over tomatoes in bowl.
Layer remaining tomato slices, sprinkling onion mixture over each layer.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: In iron skillet, over low to medium heat, heat up oil until hot.
Stir in flour, stirring continuously until dark brown.
Add 2 Tbsp. water, stirring until you paste has the consistency of peanut butter.
Meanwhile, bring to boil, 2 to 3 quart of water in large pot.
Add rue to pot and stir in until mixed.
Add onion and celery.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes, until onions turn clear.
Add shrimp and garlic.
Cook 5 more minutes, seasoning with Gumbo Fil and Tony's to taste.
Serve by pouring over servings of rice and garnish with chopped green onions.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix white sugar, brown sugar and butter or margarine. Mix eggs and vanilla in brown sugar mixture. Mix flour, baking soda, salt and chocolate chips with rest of ingredients. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in 375° preheated oven.

title: rice krispy candy
directions: Bring sugar and Karo syrup to a boil for no more than 30 seconds.
Add peanut butter and stir.
Add Rice Krispies and stir. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and butter together.
Spread over Rice Krispies mixture.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a double boiler. Add boiling water slowly and stir constantly. Cook until mixture thickens. Beat egg yolks slightly and pour some of the hot mixture over egg batter and stir vigorously. Add egg batter to double boiler and cook for
2 minutes. Remove from heat and add lemon rind, juice and butter; beat well and cool. Pour into pie shell.

title: meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Put in loaf pan.
Cover with foil; cook at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, pour other half of tomato sauce over meat.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake for 15 minutes.
Melt caramel over low heat; add margarine and milk. Spread over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, nuts and coconut over cake and caramel topping.
Pour rest of cake batter over cake and bake at 300° an additional 30 minutes.

title: bulldog gingersnaps
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Cut in butter to resemble coarse crumbs.
Stir in molasses and egg.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: wilted zucchini and red onion salad
directions: Place zucchini in a bowl; sprinkle with salt and allow to stand for 30 minutes.
Saute onion briefly.
Mix remaining ingredients; put aside.
After 30 minutes, squeeze water out of zucchini and place in a strainer until water no longer comes out. Place zucchini and onion in a bowl; pour on the desired amount of vinaigrette dressing.
Chill and serve.

title: window pane dessert
directions: Dissolve cherry, orange and lime flavor Jell-O separately using 1 cup of the boiling water for each flavor.
Add 1/2 cup of the cold water to each flavor.
Pour each flavor into its own 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm (helps to grease pan lightly). Loosen; plunge into warm water a few seconds.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Dissolve lemon flavor Jell-O and sugar in remaining 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend whipped topping into lemon flavor Jell-O.
Fold in Jell-O squares.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan.
Chill overnight in mold if so desired.
May garnish with additional Cool Whip.

title: jumbles cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add all ingredients and mix. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: mommy's apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add applesauce and dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: no stir cobbler
directions: Line pans with parchment paper.
Divide butter equally between 2 pans and melt butter in pans.
Mix dry ingredients; add milk and stir until combined thoroughly.
Pour batter over melted butter in pans.
Spoon fruit evenly over batter.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Use your favorite spaghetti sauce.
Mix all ingredients together; put in the peppers.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine. Cook broccoli and drain. Press or squeeze out water before adding to other ingredients. Combine all ingredients.
Serve warm with crackers, chips or vegetables.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Boil chicken; save 1 1/2 cups of broth.
Debone and cut chicken into cubes.

title: peanut butter cornflake squares
directions: Boil brown sugar and white syrup.
Take off stove and add peanut butter.
Add salt.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour mixture over cornflakes.
Mix well.
Butter a biscuit pan and with hands press mixture into pan, pressing together.
Cut into squares. Cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together and cook in a 350° oven.
Let it come to a simmer in oven; then cook for 15 minutes.

title: chicken alpine
directions: In greased 13 x 9-inch pan, layer according to order.
Bake 1 hour, covered and 1/2 hour, uncovered, at 350°.

title: brown bread date bars
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and shortening.
Blend well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla. Blend well.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cut in bars and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 25 bars.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets. Brown chops in skillet.
Peel and slice potatoes. Peel and slice onions very thin.
Place layer of potatoes in casserole dish. Add salt and pepper.
Add layer of onions. Place pork chops on top. Add salt, pepper and thyme.
Pour soup, diluted with 1/2 can of water on top. Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes or until done.

title: quick beef casserole
directions: Combine Beefaroni, ketchup, sour cream and cream cheese.
Mix half the cheese in dish with mixture and other half on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted or heated throughout.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Blend together and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Top with crushed nuts.

title: chili chip bake
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Remove from heat; add beans, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, 1/2 cup cheese and onion.
Set aside 1 cup corn chips.
Stir remaining corn chips into meat mixture.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with sour cream and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining corn chips on top.
Continue baking until cheese is melted. Yield: 6 servings.

title: bridal shower coconut cake
directions: For Cake:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottoms of 2 (9-inch) diameter cake pans with 2-inch high sides with waxed paper.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Using electric mixer, beat butter in large bowl until smooth.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix in vanilla and coconut extracts. Reserve 1/4 cup coconut milk for frosting.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cream together butter, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: blender avocado dip
directions: Place avocados and eggs in blender container; process until pureed.
Add remaining ingredients; process to mix well.

title: grasshopper cake
directions: Bake cake (first 5 ingredients) in 9 x 13 pan. Spray and flour according to directions on package. Cool. Frost.

title: sweet corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour until dissolved in butter.
Mix in the sour cream and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add the corn and 1/2 of the crumbled bacon and then pour the mixture into a casserole dish.
Add the remaining bacon as a topping and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
This recipe can easily be cut in half.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 10-inch quiche dish or 2-quart casserole dish with Pam. Beat eggs and sour cream in a large bowl. Stir in corn, bread crumbs, chilies, salt, pepper and shredded cheese. Pour into a prepared dish. Bake 40 minutes or until firm.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in heavy saucepan, gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Cook for 1 minute.
Beat egg yolks, gradually stir about one fourth hot mixture into yolks.
Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly, cook 30 seconds, remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Cover with meringue made with egg whites.

title: treasure salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Serve on a bed of crisp lettuce.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In soup pot, put chicken, carrots, celery, celery seed, parsley, pepper, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add water to about 2 inches above chicken to start.
Add 1 tablespoon salt.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until chicken is done.
Remove chicken; pick apart. Put chicken pieces back into soup.
Cook egg noodles; drain and add to soup.
Salt to taste.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix lemon, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Soak meat in sauce mixture, 10 to 20 minutes, then season with lemon pepper and garlic salt.
Do not oversalt.
Bake 8 to 10 hours in warm oven (with door cracked), about 1 inch.

title: vegetable stir-up
directions: Saute vegetables in skillet 3 to 4 minutes in hot oil over medium heat.
Remove vegetables from pan and set aside.
In same skillet, stir in shrimp.
Cook until shrimp turns a pink color. Return vegetables to skillet with the shrimp and add soy sauce and black pepper, stir well.
Pour in cornstarch dissolved in cold water and allow mixture to bubble about 1 minute.
Serve over fluffy cooked rice.

title: brocioluna (stuffed beef roll)
directions: Combine
garlic,
bread
crumbs,
cheese,
onions
and seasonings.
Mix
well and add a little water to make a paste. Pound round steak a little on both sides.
Lay it flat.
Brush olive
oil over steak.
Spread bread crumb mixture over steak, laying egg
slices on top.
Fold in sides of steak and roll up just as
you
would a jelly roll.
Tie securely with string or dental
floss.
Heat
cup oil in skillet, browning on all sides;
drain.
Add
about
cups of your favorite spaghetti sauce and
cook on medium heat until done, about 1 hour.
When done, remove string and cut in 1-inch slices.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown onion and meat in frying pan until all meat is brown. Add tomato sauce and simmer for a few minutes.
Add corn.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk and beat with a wire whisk until well blended (1 to 2 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes; fold in whipped topping.
Add 5 chopped Heath bars to pudding mix.
Spread 1/3 cup butterscotch sauce into crust.
Spoon pudding mixture on top. Freeze until firm (6 hours or overnight).
After frozen, drizzle caramel sauce over the top in a circle pattern.
Drizzle last chopped Heath bar.
Place back in freezer.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and milk.
Beat thoroughly.
Add lemon juice and stir until thick.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.

title: maj's magic
directions: Cut English muffins into 1/8 wedges.
Spread mixture over each and broil until cheese is brown and bubbly.
Can be prepared a few hours ahead and kept on cookie sheets in the refrigerator.
Serve them hot and see if your guests can guess what's in them.

title: butterfingers
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar and vanilla.
Mix in the flour and nuts (I use pecans).
Roll out into fingers.
Place on a nonstick cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Take out and roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Be very careful as they will break easily.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Combine dates, water and granulated sugar in saucepan.
Cook until thick (2 to 3 minutes), stirring constantly.
Cool. Thoroughly cream the butter and second two sugars; add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla. Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture, stirring until smooth after each addition.
Chill.

title: martha's mile high coconut pie
directions: Mix
cups
sugar,
cornstarch and 1 cup of milk together
and
cook
in
a	large
pan
over medium heat until mixture
is
dissolved.
Mix
together 1 cup milk, well beaten eggs and oleo.
Add to first mixture and cook until thickened. Stir constantly, then add coconut flavoring and 1 cup coconut. Mix well.
Cool
and
pour
into cooked pie shell.
Take 4 egg whites and
beat
until
stiff peaks form.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar. Pour over pie and sprinkle coconut over top.
Brown in a 300° oven.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut white bread into cubes with crusts.
Soak for 5 minutes in scalded milk.
Beat eggs slightly; add vanilla.
Add to bread mixture, blending in well.
Stir in raisins.
Pour in greased casserole and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven or until knife comes out clean.
Sometimes I will use raisin bread and leave out the raisins.

title: wild rice chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in large skillet; blend in flour, salt and pepper cook until smooth and bubbly over low heat. Remove from heat add chicken broth and milk.
Return to heat, bring to boil, stirring constantly one minute or so.
Add remaining ingredients pour into 9 by 13 pan or two small casseroles.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.
May be doubled for serving 24.

title: orange blossom cupcakes
directions: Use any yellow cake mix and follow directions.
Put batter in small muffin tin and bake.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in flour and cook until smooth.
Add milk and cook until mixture thickens.
Add salt, chili powder, onion and green pepper, stirring well.
Wash hominy and drain. Stir in and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fill pastry lined pan.
Bake in preheated slow oven (300°) for 1 hour or until barely set.
Cool; top with whipped cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: eye opening baked potatoes
directions: Prick each potato; microwave for approximately 6 to 8 minutes. Remove and slice 2/3 of the way through in 1/2-inch sections.
Melt margarine; mix with onion soup mix and diced jalapeno peppers. Gently spread apart potato and pour mixture between each section. Quickly wrap in foil and place on grill.
Cook for approximately 10 minutes; turn and cook another 10 minutes, until soft.

title: oyster stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, Tabasco sauce and cold water.
Blend to a smooth paste.
Stir in oysters and liquid. Add butter.
Simmer over very low heat 5 minutes, just until edges of oysters curl, stirring gently. Combine milk and cream; scald and pour into oysters. Remove from heat and cover.
Let stand 15 minutes to blend flavors.
Heat soup tureen and dishes.
Reheat stew briefly to serving temperature.
Pour into tureen. Dash with paprika on top.
Pass crackers.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Place in shallow dish.
Mix water, onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper. Pour over carrots.
Dash with paprika.

title: chicken salad for sandwiches
directions: Mix ingredients with salad dressing and pickle juice to make spreading consistency.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Cream together sugar and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into crust and spread pie filling on top.
Chill 4 hours.

title: best-ever brownies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 45 seconds.
Add chocolate chips and beat until smooth.
Pour hot frosting on warm brownies.
Cut into bars when cool.
Freeze well.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter or oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thick.
(Add 1 pound of cooked hamburger for complete dinner.)
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: cranberry walnut apple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 4 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Combine apples, sugar and oil in a medium bowl.
Add egg.
Mix well. Combine dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add to apple mixture. Stir well.
Stir in cranberries and walnuts.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake for 1 hour until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta to slightly firm and let cool slightly.
Mix vegetables and seasoning together and then add to pasta.
Toss together, then add dressing.
Toss until everything is coated with dressing.
Put in the refrigerator overnight.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: cheese soup
directions: Place the potatoes, carrots, broccoli, onoin and pepper in a large saucepan.
Add the water, cover and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for about 15 minutes, or until veggies are tender, not mushy.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Follow regular directions on the cake mix but bake on a large cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes. After it is cool, mix milk with instant pudding.
Beat in cream cheese (room temperature). Add Cool Whip.
Mix well and spread on top of cooled cake.
Sprinkle on the well drained pineapple.
Last sprinkle on the Angel Flake coconut all over the top of the cake.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Melt oleo; add 1 egg and cake mix.
Mix well (will be lumpy); set aside.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour this mixture over the top of the cake mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hot dog pizzas(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place muffin halves, cut side up, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each with 1 tablespoon tomato soup. Arrange 6 hot dog slices on each muffin half; sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 pizzas.

title: heavenly potatoes
directions: Heat soup and oleo.
Blend in sour cream.
Grease casserole dish.
Alternate layers of potatoes, onion and soup mixture.
Top with crushed corn flake crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple toast
directions: Spread bread with butter.
Put apple on top of bread. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Broil 1 minute.

title: honey garlic pork
directions: Combine ingredients except pork. Pour over pork and marinate 4 to 24 hours.
Broil 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sue's pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening together.

title: grandma's coconut pies(makes 2)
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour in pie crust. Cook about 45 minutes.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Slice chiles lengthwise.
Layer half of the chiles in an 8-inch casserole, greased.
Top with half the cheese.
Repeat this layering with remaining chiles and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over chile mixture.
Sprinkle top of casserole with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: german chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Mix in sugar and beat.
Add vanilla.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time; beat.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture and 2/3 cup black walnuts.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in balls, then roll in 10x sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 14 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix well the Cool Whip and pudding (straight from the package).
Add cottage cheese, pineapple, nuts and marshmallows. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: tortellini with olive oil and basil
directions: Boil the peas with the tortellini according to the tortellini package instructions, usually 10 minutes.
In large glass bowl, mix both virgin olive and pure olive oils, balsamic vinegar, red pepper, shallot and basil.
After draining the tortellini and peas, add to olive oil mixture and stir.
Place in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Heat and serve.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain both cans of artichokes and then cut or chop them into bite sized pieces.
Add hot sauce to artichokes (amount determined by individual taste).
Spread artichoke/hot sauce mixture in bottom of baking dish and cover with diced chiles.
Spread thin layer of mayonnaise on top.
Spread shredded cheese over mayonnaise.
Bake until bubbly.

title: whole wheat bulgar bread
directions: Mix together bulgar, molasses, honey, salt, shortening, 2 cups whole wheat flour and yeast.
Add warm water and mix thoroughly. Add other cup whole wheat flour, cornmeal and oatmeal.
Mix well. Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover, let rise in warm place (80° to 85°), free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down.
Let dough rise a second time, about 45 minutes.
Punch dough down, divide in halves and shape into loaves.
Place in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large bowl beat 1/2 cup powdered sugar, butter and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, almonds and salt; mix until dough forms.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set but not brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Cool slightly; roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely. Re-roll in powdered sugar.
Yield:
5 dozen cookies.

title: yummy oatmeal
directions: In a bowl, pour 1/4 cup instant oatmeal and 1/2 cup water. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Sprinkle on top brown sugar, assorted ice cream, sprinkle toppings, chocolate chips, etc.
A sweet tooth delight.

title: calico beans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Brown bacon and hamburger; drain. Blend with all of the remaining ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish for 1 1/2 hours.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add chocolate, rum and vanilla.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating 3 to 5 minutes.
Top with whipped cream. Pour into baked crust.
Chill for 3 to 5 hours.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add cornstarch and sugar.
Blend in milk and other ingredients.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: tuna-noodle crispy
directions: Heat cheese, soup and milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add noodles, tuna and pepper; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole; top with crackers tossed with margarine.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: slow cooker chili
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef.
Then combine with all other ingredients and cook in slow cooker for 3 hours on low setting.

title: stuffed french loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice bread in half lengthwise and slightly hollow out both halves, leaving 1/2-inch thick layer of bread.
Place bread crumbs in blender or processor and process 15 to 20 seconds until fine.
Set aside.
Cook sausage, onion and garlic in heavy skillet over medium heat until meat is browned; drain.
In large bowl combine bread crumbs, meat mixture, egg, mustard and parsley.
Using blender or processor, process cheese, olive oil, 2 tablespoons mustard and peppers until mixture forms a paste, about 1 minute.
Spread cheese mixture over inside of each bread half.
Spoon meat mixture into cavity of each bread half. Place halves together and wrap in foil.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until well heated.
Cut into 1-inch slices.

title: cherry cream cheese cake
directions: Cook margarine and sugar over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Mix in graham crackers. Press evenly and firmly in pie pan to form crust.
Chill.

title: chili with beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Stir in seasoning, tomato sauce, tomatoes and kidney beans.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes on stove top.
Add chili powder to taste.
Can put in crock-pot and let cook on low 4 to 5 hours.
Stir occasionally until ready to eat.
Serve with shredded cheese, sour cream and saltine crackers or browned French bread.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Mix with hot water to taste.

title: raw apple pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except apples and nuts.
Mix well. Add apples and nuts,
Mix well again.
Pour into greased and floured bundt or tube pan.
Bake 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.

title: proud bird honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar, honey, mustard, vinegar, onion and parsley. Blend in oil.
Chill about 1 hour before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Wash brisket under cold water, then place in a pan and cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Drain. Cover with fresh boiling water and simmer until meat is tender.

title: pecan crackers
directions: Break crackers apart and place on cookie sheet with cinnamon side facing up.
Top each cracker with 2 pecan halves.
Boil sugar and butter over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers to coat evenly.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes and vegetable packets
directions: Lightly oil two 15-inch long strips of foil.
Mix potatoes, onions and bell pepper in a bowl.
Divide mixture between the 2 pieces of foil, placing on one end.
Dot with butter.
Fold other end of foil over potatoes, then fold edges over a few times to seal.

title: tortilla roll-ups(with spinach dip filling)
directions: Mix spinach (thawed and squeezed dry), mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing mix.
Stir to mix well.
Spread on large flour tortilla.
Roll up and wrap in plastic wrap.
Recipe is enough for 5 or 6 tortillas.
Chill 2 hours or longer.
Before serving, slice in 1/2-inch slices and serve as appetizers.

title: foil wrapped dinners
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut meat into 1-inch pieces.
Separate frozen peas; drain.
Tear off 4 pieces heavy-duty foil, 18 x 15 inches.
On center of each piece, place 1 carrot, thinly sliced, 1 potato, cut in quarters and 1/4 of meat.
Stir together mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Spoon mixture over meat and top with peas.
Wrap securely.

title: m-m-m good bars
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter; add cornflakes.
Press into well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into bars and enjoy!

title: best bet strawberry pie
directions: Thicken water, sugar and cornstarch on stove.
Add 4 tablespoons strawberry jello; let cool.
(May add red food coloring for more color if you wish.)
Bake pie shell.
Fill the shell with strawberries.
Cover strawberries with filling.
Let set in refrigerator until chilled.
Cover with cream or Cool Whip.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in greased bowl.

title: mock chicken meat balls(serves 4)
directions: Mix well and form into balls the size of an egg.
Brown on all sides.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix cereal, brown sugar and margarine.
Press evenly in oiled 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Melt butter, add flour and combine.
Add milk and cook until very thick, stirring constantly.
Add salmon and seasoning and chill thoroughly.
Form into small rounds about 1/2 inch thick. Roll in crumbs, then in slightly beaten egg and in cracker crumbs again. Chill.
Fry in deep fat until brown.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Drain peppers and cut open; remove seeds and pat dry.
Line the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan with the peppers. Preheat oven to 350° or 375°.
Cover peppers with the grated cheeses.
Mix tomato sauce, evaporated milk, egg yolks, flour, salt and pepper; set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into tomato sauce mixture.
Spread over cheeses.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana loaf
directions: Mix together the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in the buttermilk and bananas.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt and stir in.
Blend in the nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: old fashioned cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 pan in a 325° oven. Combine milk, sugar and flour. Pour over the melted butter. Add fruit; do not stir. Bake for about an hour or until golden brown.

title: sangria (delicious)
directions: About 15 minutes before serving or early in day:

title: puffy omelet
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until peaks form.
In separate bowl, mix yolks, water and mayonnaise until combined. Fold yolks into egg whites.
Melt butter in skillet at medium heat.
Add mixture and cook for 10 minutes.
Take skillet off heat and bake in oven at 400° for 7 minutes.
During last 2 minutes in oven, put cheese on top.
Serves 4.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour and spices into meat with hammer. Cut into serving size pieces. Brown in shortening.
Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Cut up and fry bacon until almost crisp.
Place bacon in a bowl.
In skillet with bacon drippings, add onions, brown sugar, garlic powder, dry mustard, vinegar and pepper.
Cook at low heat for 20 minutes, covered.
Mix all beans, bacon and onion mixture together well.
Bake in a covered 3-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour, perhaps longer, but not until it's dried out.
(Dish can also be cooked in a crock-pot for 6 hours on low.)

title: sharon's souper casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: yassa lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Season with garlic, chilies, ginger and salt.
Cover chicken with lemon juice and let marinate for 2 to 3 hours.
When ready to prepare, heat oil in a large frypan.
Pour off marinade and reserve.
Pat chicken pieces dry.
Brown in oil and transfer to a plate.
Pour off oil, leaving 2 tablespoons.
Return chicken to frypan and add marinade; bring to a fast boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer until chicken is tender, about 30 minutes.
Ten minutes before chicken is done, add onions; let cook until slightly crisp.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: egg salad triangles
directions: Combine chopped eggs, chopped olives and green onion.
Stir in mayonnaise or salad dressing and mustard.
Remove crust; spread 1/4 cup on each slice.
Cut bread into triangles.
Makes 20 sandwiches.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Mix in all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: egg drink
directions: Mix well in a mixer the eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Serve cold with an ice cube.

title: mandarin whip
directions: Combine cottage cheese, Cool Whip, oranges and pineapple. Sprinkle in jello.
Mix.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone; in 1/2 cup butter, cook onions, celery and bell peppers. Cook spaghetti; rinse and mix in soup, tomatoes, pimentos and 1 cup chicken broth. Stir in chicken and 1/2 package of grated cheese. Mix well and pour into 2 big casseroles. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: mixed baked beans
directions: Brown bacon; crumble and set aside.
In bacon drippings, saute diced onions; drain off fat.
Add dry mustard, salt, garlic powder, vinegar, brown sugar and molasses.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add all the drained beans.
Bake for 2 hours at 250° or in a crock-pot for 4 to 5 hours until thick.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in skillet until tortilla puffs up a little. On each tortilla sprinkle grated cheese, onion, chicken and sauce (sauce is cream of chicken soup mixed with milk and green chiles). Roll filled tortillas and place in casserole dish. Top with remaining grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
To cook in crock pot:
Leave tortillas flat.
Layer tortillas, chicken, onion, sauce and cheese.
After layering, top with more grated cheese.
Cook 5 to 8 hours on low or 3 hours on high.

title: cheesy cornbread(serves 9)
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Saute onions in butter. Prepare mix per directions but use the corn for milk. Pour onions on top of mix. Sprinkle cheese on top the last 5 minutes. Bake 30 minutes in 9 x 9 pan.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring all ingredients to rolling boil.
Boil for 10 minutes. Put in clean jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: chocolate peppermint cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Combine butter and water in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in soda.
Add flour mixture, stirring well.
Stir in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla extract.
Spoon into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with peppermint patties and bake 2 additional minutes.
Gently spread melted candy over cake.
Spread Chocolate Frosting over top.

title: janet's spaghetti
directions: Mix all sauce ingredients; simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low overnight.

title: peanut butter stuffed apples
directions: Combine peanut butter with 1 or more of the next 5 ingredients.
Stuff apples with about 2 tablespoons filling.
Wrap in foil.
These are great for camping, whole or sliced.
Kids and grownups love them!

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill overnight.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Crush the crackers to fine powder.
Melt the marshmallows and margarine.
Chip up pecans, cherries and raisins.
Use the juice. Then mix it all by hand until blended evenly.
Pack it all back in graham box and put in refrigerator.
Eat next day, or month.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut and steam squash in 1/2 cup water and 1/4 cup sugar. Place squash, undrained, in a good size baking dish.
Beat egg into milk and pour over squash.
Saute onion in butter and add. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in torn-up fresh bread to leave little liquid standing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
(Good substitute for stuffing.)

title: apple-orange cider
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot.
Serve with cinnamon sticks, if desired.
Yields 1 quart.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Cream butter, add sugar gradually and mix well. Add well beaten egg yolk, flavoring, and flour. Shape into balls about the size of a walnut. Dip in unbeaten egg whites, then in finely chopped nuts. Dent in center with a thimble. Place on baking sheet and bake at 350 degrees for five minutes; dent again. At Christmas, can put cherry in dent.
Bake 12-15 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Add chili beans.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Microwave for about 5 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and cold water.
Cook slowly until thick and clear.
Stir in the strawberry gelatin.
Arrange fresh strawberries on a cooled, baked pie crust.
Pour mixture over strawberries.
Chill in refrigerator several hours.
Cover with whipped cream, if desired.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Roll in balls; flatten with fork tines dipped in sugar or roll in balls.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 13 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with Hershey Kisses while still hot.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water according to package directions. Melt cream cheese in hot gelatin. Set in refrigerator until it begins to thicken. Add pineapple and return to refrigerator. When gelatin mixture is almost set, fold in whipped topping. Add nuts. Put in mold or bowl and return to refrigerator until completely set.

title: easy beef and vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and onion in large pot.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until macaroni and vegetables are soft, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cool squash and mash; saute onion and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Mix with other ingredients reserving a small amount of cheese and cracker crumbs for garnish.
Put in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Garnish with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry hamburg, pepper and onion.
Drain.
Mix vinegar, brown sugar and ketchup to hamburger mixture.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix milk, vinegar and mustard together, then add all other ingredients.
Make the day before if needed.

title: broccoli fruit salad
directions: Mix together first four ingredients. Let sit overnight.

title: peanut butter pies
directions: Bake and cool
2 pie shells.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into 2 pie shells.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: hamburger, cheese and noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions together; drain.
Cook noodles until tender.
Layer meat, noodles, sauce and cheese.
Layer again, making cheese the top layer.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ham and cheese snack
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescents into two rectangles. Place in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press over bottom and 1/4 inch up on sides to form crust.
Spread mixture over crust. Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake until golden brown, 18 to 25 minutes.
Cut into pieces and serve.

title: oooohbleck
directions: Mix cornstarch and water in approximately 2 to 1 ratio.
You should be able to roll mixture into ball and then let drip through your fingers.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Store in tightly covered container in cool place.

title: apricot bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in rolled oats and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Put 2/3 of crumb mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with preserves; cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes or until browned.
Cool; cut in bars or squares.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Substitute mandarin oranges (juice included) instead of water. Prepare per directions on box.

title: snappy green beans
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble. Cook onion with basil in drippings until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat.
Stir and garnish with bacon.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken with honey mustard
directions: In a bowl, mix honey, mustard and soy sauce.
Spread honey mix to chicken breast.
Sprinkle sesame seed to chicken.
Broil chicken for about 15 minutes or until done.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Scald milk in top part of double boiler.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt; blend thoroughly.
Pour part of the milk over dry ingredients, stirring constantly.
Gradually add all the milk. Return to double boiler; cook, stirring until thickened.
Beat egg yolks.
Add a little of the hot mixture from the double boiler; mix.
Put this in double boiler with rest of hot mixture; cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice, rind and butter; stir until smooth.
Cool.
Fold in the egg white which has been beaten stiff.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: salmon pate spread
directions: Debone salmon.
Mix all ingredients. Serve with crackers.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove and cool on a wire rack.
Spoon hot glaze over warm cake.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cocoa in flour.
Mix 2 teaspoons of buttermilk with red food coloring.
Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add red mix.
Alternate flour and buttermilk and mix well.
Fold in soda and vinegar. Pour in three 8-inch cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (40 minutes for sheet cake).

title: favorite beverage
directions: Combine with water following directions on cans.
Mix with ice and serve.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to a boil.
Cool until thick and clear.
Add cool jello.
Fill crust with frozen berries.
Pour jello over top.

title: simmering potpourri
directions: Add all ingredients in an open pan.
Simmer on stove.
Add water as needed.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook macaroni.
Cut up tomatoes.
In a 10-inch skillet, stir together undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, green pepper, sugar, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: herbed scramble(beans and tomatoes)
directions: Lightly saute the garlic and onion in the oil.
Remove the pieces of garlic.
Add tomato; cover and simmer until soft. Arrange the beans on top of the tomato; salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add basil.
Beat the egg slightly and pour over the beans.
Toss until egg is cooked and blended throughout.

title: chicken on the nest
directions: Wrap bacon around chicken.
Place in Pyrex dish on bed of chipped beef (2 or 3 pieces).
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except cinnamon sugar mixture.
Mix well for about 5 minutes.
Grease Bundt pan liberally with margarine and coat sides with some of cinnamon sugar mixture (enough to coat).
Pour 1/2 of batter in pan. Sprinkle with rest of cinnamon sugar mix.
Pour remaining batter into pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Leave in pan 15 minutes to cool.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: In a small bowl, combine tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, Lipton soup mix, herb stuffing mix, bell pepper, ground meat, salt and pepper. Add half of tomato sauce mixture and stir thoroughly.
Place meat mixture in ring mold or 2-quart microwave-proof round casserole dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 12 to 14 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Great!

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Mix meat, tomato soup, onion juice and Worcestershire sauce. Form into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Put in foil and refrigerate. Remove and ice with onion dip or cream cheese, softened. Cover with sliced olives. Spread on crackers.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Mix butter, egg, vanilla, flour and sugars; bake in an ungreased 13 x 7-inch pan at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: greg's orange chicken
directions: Pre-mix flour, cinnamon and parsley in small container. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in frying pan; add chicken and brown on both sides.
Remove from pan.
Add pre-mixed ingredients to the frying pan, along with the garlic. Stir chicken in slowly, then add orange juice.
Stir well; bring to a boil.
Then reduce heat to medium; cover and simmer for 50 minutes.
Add mandarin oranges and simmer 10 minutes more.

title: bacon sticks
directions: Wrap 1 slice bacon diagonally around each bread stick, overlapping edges.
Roll in cheese.
Arrange on ridged microwave tray.
Microwave for 7 to 8 minutes or until bacon is done to taste.
Roll in cheese.
Cool to room temperature.
Makes 16 servings.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Combine in blender until thick and smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/4 cups or is equal to 14-ounce can.
Can be thinned with a few drops of water if it gets too thick in refrigerator.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese. Pour half the mixture in well-greased pan and sprinkle with cheese. Add other half of mixture. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Rinse,	and
drain the Ranch Style beans.
Assemble the salad and pour on the Catalina dressing.	Good!

title: chewie bread
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Melt butter and remove from heat.
Add sugar.
Stir until blended.
Add the flour and pecans.
Spread in pan, bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in bars while warm.

title: cherry crumble
directions: Spread pie filling in 9-inch pan.
Cut butter into dry muffin or cake mix to form crumbs.
Sprinkle over cherry mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 9 servings.

title: best seafood pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If it isn't moist enough, add more mayonnaise. Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Serve cold on lettuce.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients until thin.
Place cleaned shrimp, split up back and deveined, in the mixture.
Remove 1 at a time; roll in corn meal.
Drop in hot cooking oil.
Cook to light brown.

title: date and nut squares
directions: Melt shortening and cool.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine dates and nuts with flour mixture.
Beat eggs until light and add to cooled melted shortening.
Add this to flour/date mixture and mix well. Bake in a well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter or oleo and butterscotch morsels in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients into mixture and add walnuts if desired.
Put into greased pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, butter and eggs.
Add flour and sugar. Beat until smooth.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix
well
and
add
to starter.
Allow to stand out of refrigerator all
day.
At
end
of
day,
take
out
1 cup of starter
to
use in making bread.
Return remaining starter to refrigerator
for 3 to 5 days.
Feed again and make bread.
If not making bread, give to a friend or throw away 1 cup starter every 3 to 5 days.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook meat with onion and garlic until no longer pink; drain.
Add beans, pepper, tomato sauce, taco sauce, salt and oregano; simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon 1 cup meat mixture evenly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer tortillas over sauce; top with remaining meat mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Cover with remaining tortillas and meat mixture.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 20 minutes; uncover.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.
Garnish with sour cream.

title: zucchini garden casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange half the tomatoes on the bottom.
Arrange half the zucchini over tomatoes and sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt.

title: three way dip
directions: Beat the cottage cheese and Blue cheese at highest speed of mixer until fairly smooth. Beat in onion, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice. Gently fold in sour cream.
Cover and chill. Serve with crackers or vegetable "dippers."
Dip may also be used as a salad dressing or served on baking potatoes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and boiling water in saucepan and cook until clear.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and stir in jello; let cool.
Pour over strawberries arranged in a baked pie shell and refrigerate until filling is firm, approximately 1 hour.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add honey, vanilla, bourbon, salt and spices. Blend well.
Add fruits, nuts and raisins.
Stir graham crackers into mixture.
Pack into loaf pans with wax paper lined.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate 7 days before Christmas.

title: wedding mints
directions: Blend cream cheese and flavoring.
Mix in sugar to consistency of pie dough.
Divide into pieces for as many colors needed.
Add color (use toothpick or dropper).
Knead dough and make small balls.
Dip balls into sugar and press into molds.
Air dry on wax paper several hours.
Makes approximately 165 mints.

title: deer roast
directions: Soak deer meat 2 to 4 hours in ice cold salt water.
Preheat oven to 225°.
Place meat in small roasting pan with a good tight fitting lid.
Pour 1/3 to 1/2 package of onion soup dip mix onto the meat.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Seal foil on roaster pan.
Place lid over foil to insure holding steam in.
Allow to bake 3 to 4 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix sugar, pecans, butter, flour and oatmeal well and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Crumble mixture while still hot (use fork).
Place 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch lightly buttered baking dish.
(Set aside remaining mixture.)
Pat down in dish and let cool completely.

title: potato and egg burritos
directions: Peel and slice potatoes (thin). Cook in small amount of shortening until brown. Add onion, then stir in eggs. Warm tortillas and fill with egg/potato mixture.

title: homemade vanilla extract
directions: Combine brandy and beans in a jar with a tight fitting lid. Let stand 3 months shaking 3 times a week.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix flour, soda and cream of tartar well.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Roll out in 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: farmer's cookies
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients into bowl.
Work in oleo (2 soft sticks) as you do for pie crust.
In small bowl, beat eggs with fork slightly.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and lemon extract to eggs. Add this mixture to flour and oleo mixture.
Blend well.
Dough will be sticky.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
Roll out on floured board.
Flour rolling pin.
Cut with floured cutter.
Sprinkle cookies with sugar before baking at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes depending on thickness of cookie.
Use large cookie cutter.
Serve with butter or jam.

title: mushroom crescents
directions: Mix above ingredients (except crescent rolls) in a small bowl. Open crescent rolls to make 4 rectangles.
Spread mixture of ingredients onto each triangle.
Jelly roll the rectangles.
Slice 1/4-inch section from rolled ends.
Brush the top with beaten egg, bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix according to directions on cake box.

title: peppery cheese biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well. Combine buttermilk and oil; add to dry ingredients.
Stir with a fork just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 3 to 4 times. Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut into rounds with a 1 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on an ungreased baking sheet; lightly coat tops of biscuits with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill crock-pot with apples.
Cook 18 hours on slow.
Do not lift lid.
Put the cooked apples through food mill if a smooth consistency is desired.
Put apples back in crock-pot.
Add sugar, cloves and cinnamon.
Cook 4 more hours.
Jar as usual.
Yield: about 2 quarts.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and vegetables; cook 30 minutes longer.
Add cheese and soup.
Simmer until cheese is melted.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Use 1/4 cup of mixture in place of 1 egg.
Yield:
1/2 cup.
Per serving (1/4 cup): calories, 100; fat, 6 g; sodium, 0; cholesterol, 0. Use 1/4 cup to replace each whole egg in most recipes.
In recipes calling for up to 2 egg yolks, use 1/4 cup per yolk.
Once made, refrigerate and use in 7 days.

title: toffee crunch cookies
directions: Combine and sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter or margarine.
Add sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Blend in chopped candy bars and pecans.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Simmer meat, tomatoes and seasonings 2 hours.
Add spaghetti, which has been cooked.
Let simmer for 1/2 hour and serve with grated cheese.

title: candy bar cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, walnuts, 2 tablespoons sugar and oleo; mix well.
Firmly press mixture into bottom and sides of an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Break candy into several pieces; melt in double boiler or microwave.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cocoa and salt; gradually add to cream cheese, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add melted chocolate; beat until blended.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla, blending well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Turn off oven; let cheesecake stand in closed oven 30 minutes.
Let cool at room temperature, then chill.
Remove sides of spring-form pan; spread Sour Cream Topping and sprinkle with walnuts.
Yield:
1 (8-inch) cheesecake.

title: no sugar grape jelly
directions: Mix grape juice and tapioca together.
Let stand 10 to 20 minutes.
Put on low heat, stirring constantly until it comes to a rolling boil.
Take off heat and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add Equal sweetener.
Makes 1 pint.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet over medium heat.
Saute onion and mushrooms until onion is transparent. Stir in soup, milk, turkey and spaghetti.
Cook until heated throughout.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat under broiler just until cheese is browned, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lavender punch(only made at christmastime)
directions: In saucepan, combine water, cinnamon sticks and cloves and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes. Chill overnight or at least a few hours; strain.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Take vanilla, 1/4 cup strawberry juice, sugar and cream cheese and blend until smooth.
Stir into whipped cream and strawberries. Put into shell.

title: baked cherry-pineapple dessert
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple well.
Place fruit in buttered 12 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Spread dry cake mix evenly over fruit.
Sprinkle with pecans and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: ham, potato and onion soup
directions: Cook potatoes in enough water to barely cover until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and potatoes, undrained.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens. Add ham and cheese; stir to melt cheese.
Makes
a large pot of soup.

title: lisa's caramel corn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in Karo syrup and sugar.
Boil for 13 minutes on medium heat.
Add vanilla.
Stir and pour over corn. Stir until corn is well coated.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts at 300° for 45 minutes.
Partially cook broccoli spears.
Mix together soup, Miracle Whip, curry and lemon juice.
Drain broccoli.
Place broccoli, side by side, on bottom of baking dish or pan.
Place cooked chicken on top of broccoli. Spoon soup mixture on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Roll cheese inside ham.
Roll this inside chicken breasts and secure with toothpicks.
Roll chicken in flour and paprika.
Brown all sides of chicken in butter on medium heat.
Add prepared bouillon or broth and wine.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or low heat.
Remove chicken from pan and place on plate.
Remove toothpicks.
In a separate bowl mix cream and cornstarch.
Add mixture to drippings in pan.
Stir constantly on medium heat until thick.
Pour gravy over chicken and serve.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and chill.

title: fresh peach crisp
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Cut in butter and set aside.
Peel and slice peaches (about 4 cups).
Arrange peaches in 8-inch square baking dish and sprinkle flour mixture evenly over peaches.
Dust with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes. Delicious served warm with ice cream.

title: gazpacho
directions: Chop vegetables.
Add to juice mixed with oil and seasonings adjusted to taste.

title: kristin's cupcakes
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat with beater until well blended.
Pour batter into cake pan or cupcake tin. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: caraway seed meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, eggs, bread crumbs, milk, salt, pepper, allspice, nutmeg, brown sugar and caraway seed.
Use a teaspoon to form balls.
Cook the balls in the butter in a frying pan.
Remove balls.
Add the bouillon, flour and water to the pan and stir until thick.
Put the balls back in, cook for 20 minutes and serve immediately.
Makes a lot, 36 meatballs.

title: val's deviled eggs turnover
directions: Peel eggs; cut in half lengthwise.
Remove egg yolk; put in bowl with mayonnaise, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Mix on high speed until smooth enough.
Spoon egg mixture into egg whites.

Now here comes the "turn over" part; if taking these yummies for pot luck, make sure if you transport in anything other than a special devil egg container, then you "turn over" the now upside down eggs.
(It happens every time to me!)

title: light beef stroganoff
directions: Slice the steak across the grain in 1/2-inch strips. Saute the onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add steak and mushrooms. Cook, stirring constantly, until steak is browned. Add wine. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Dissolve cornstarch in broth. Stir into beef mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened. Remove from heat.
Stir in pepper, dill weed and yogurt.
Toss parsley with noodles.
Contains 291 calories and 110 mg.
cholesterol.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Bake chicken with lime juice and dill weed at 350° temperature for 30 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle diced green pepper over chicken.
Pour over creamy cucumber salad dressing generously. Return to oven for 15 minutes more.
Delicious!

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and bake in two 9-inch greased and floured round cake pans. Let cake cool and then split each layer in half. Mix remaining ingredients and spread this mixture between layers and on top and sides of cake and place in air tight container for three days in refrigerator.
Cake can be eaten immediately, but it is recommended that it set 3 days in the refrigerator.

title: salad garnet
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Can also do with pineapple, peaches and strawberries.

title: doi(a dessert from india; tastes like cheesecake.)
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Set pan into larger pan with 1 to 2-inches of water.
Bake at 200° to 225° for 1 1/2 hours, or until set.
Serve with fruit (peaches, strawberries, blueberries, etc.).
Good cold or warm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Debone and cut into chunks.
Heat together chicken, peas, celery, soup, milk, onions, celery and chicken broth.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 1/2 stuffing mixture.
Pour on chicken mixture, then add Cheddar cheese.
Top with the other 1/2 stuffing mixture.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together everything except cracker crumbs and margarine. Melt margarine and stir into cracker crumbs.
Spread over vegetable mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Combine ingredients; drop in round.
Fry few minutes in butter/margarine.

title: blueberry bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar, oleo and pecans.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together the apples and sugar.
Combine the oil, nuts, egg and vanilla and add to the apples.
Mix and sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt and add to the mixture.
Put into greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until it shrinks from edge of pan.
Sift a tablespoon of powdered sugar on top, if desired.

title: pinto bean pies
directions: Mash pinto beans; add sugar.
Beat eggs and add to mixture. Add coconut, vanilla and pecans; mix well.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie crusts and bake in preheated oven 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300°.
These pies freeze well.

title: joyce's ham roll-up
directions: Spread cheese and chives on slices of ham and roll-up.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Slice 1 inch thick and put on tray with toothpick.
Very pretty and good.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour undrained pineapple into cake pan.
Add pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix on top; sprinkle on nuts.
Put pats of margarine on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 9 day slaw
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, oil and seasonings in small saucepan; bring to a boil for a second.
Pour over slaw.
Let set overnight. Keep in a covered dish in refrigerator.

title: banana almond oatcakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine melted butter, banana, brown sugar, salt, egg, flour, oats, baking powder, almonds and milk.
Beat until well-blended and let sit for 10 minutes or more (it can be stored overnight in refrigerator).
Batter will be thicker than normal pancake batter.
If too thick, stir in small amount of water.

title: easy strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Add slightly thawed strawberries.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
If strawberries are still partly frozen, it will thicken in 10 minutes.
Watch closely.
Fold in Dream Whip.

title: salad pizza
directions: Spread rolls on ungreased cookie sheet and cook until brown. Blend cream cheese, Ranch dressing mix and mayonnaise.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight and cut in squares.

title: presto pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sliver onion, pepper and olives. Crumble cheese; sprinkle 2/3 over bread shells.
Top with red pepper, onion and olives.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin souffle
directions: After mixing your ingredients together, fold in egg whites. Pour everything into a spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight, put on a plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Peel.
Beat softened cream cheese, sour cream and potatoes until light and fluffy (season to taste with garlic salt and chives).
Spoon into 2-quart casserole. Brush with softened butter; sprinkle with parsley, bacon bits and paprika.
Brown at 350° for 30 minutes (longer if refrigerated ahead of time).
Serves 8.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and beat thoroughly.
Mix milk and molasses together with shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: ginger nuts
directions: In medium mixing bowl, beat egg white with the cold water until frothy.
Add mixed nuts and stir until well combined.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together the sugar, lemon peel and ginger root.
Pour the sugar mixture over nut mixture.
Toss until evenly coated.
Spread nuts in single layer in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool nuts in pan, stirring once.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger and onion in skillet.
Drain well.
Add catsup, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt and water to meat mixture.
Stir.
Drain kidney and baby lima beans and add to mixture.
Add pork and beans, do not drain these.
Mix well.
Put in 2-quart buttered casserole and bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°. Can also be put in a crock-pot.

title: jake's nacho dip
directions: Brown meats and onion in skillet; drain.
Melt cheeses down on Low power in microwave.
Combine all.
Serve warm in crock-pot with scoop tostados or whatever.

title: corn-stuffed pork chops
directions: Season chops
with
salt
and
pepper.	Cook celery and onion in butter
until
tender,
but not brown.
In large bowl combine the
bread	crumbs,
drained
corn,
salt,	sage
and pepper.
Add celery
and onion; mix well.
Spoon about 1/3 cup of stuffing mixture
into each chop.
Place stuffed chops in a 15 x 10	x 1-inch baking pan.	Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove
foil.
Continue baking 30 to 35 minutes more or until
meat is tender.
Spoon pan juices over meat and sprinkle with paprika.

title: beadie's sweet potato coffee can cakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Fill 4 pound coffee cans 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Replace lids to keep.
May freeze wrapped in foil.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups, milk and rice.
Baste chicken with butter.
Lay chicken on soup-rice mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: company vegetables
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to directions on packages. Drain.
Combine with other ingredients in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Stir 2 or 3 times while baking.
Serves 12.

title: steak and kidney pie
directions: Prepare pie crust as directed on the box.
Refrigerate.
Roll chuck strips in the 1/4 cup flour on waxed paper. Melt butter in hot skillet; add chuck and brown on all sides.
Arrange strips in a 13
x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover kidney with cold water. Let stand for 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Peel onions and slice thinly (about 5 cups).
Put butter in 4-quart pan; melt and add onions and pepper.
Saute mixture until onions are golden brown.
Sprinkle with flour and stir.
Add beef broth and bay leaves and bring to boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to low and cook uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes.
Pour soup into tureen, casserole or into individual soup bowls.
