Toast the bread and arrange toast on top of soup; cover with 2 cheeses and place in oven at 425° until cheese melts
and serve.

title: cheese hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cheddar cheese and corn flakes together.
Spoon into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, then with corn flakes.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast for the guy's(breakfast)
directions: Night before:
Cook sausage and slice.
Grease 9x13 inch pan. Put all ingredients in pan.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake in a cast-iron skillet, greased well.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: Add salt to water and bring to boil.
Add shrimp and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes, depending on size of shrimp.
(Shrimp is cooked when opaque in center when tested by cutting in half.)
Drain shrimp.
Rinse shrimp thoroughly under cold running water.

title: sunshine bait for dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients until it is very thick, like concrete that is setting up.
Line a cookie sheet with a lightly greased piece of aluminum foil.
Pour in the cookie mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
When done, peel off the foil and break into pieces. Refrigerate until use or freeze in packages to suit your needs.

title: grape cucumber salad
directions: Arrange grapes and cucumber on lettuce in salad bowl.
Mix the next five ingredients.
Stir into yogurt and spoon over salad. Yields six servings.

title: milk shake
directions: Put milk and fruit in blender and blend well.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Use a big pot. Heat oil and cook chopped onion. Put in the ground beef; let cook until brown. Add garlic salt, oregano, sugar and a couple dashes of pepper. Add the tomatoes, paste and water. Cook slowly for about 3 hours.
The sauce should be thick. Stir frequently to prevent scorching. Makes 8 servings.

title: french chocolate
directions: Heat chocolate pieces, corn syrup and water over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in vanilla; chill.

title: pear salad
directions: Prepare jello with hot and cold water; let jello reach beginning stage to set.
Mix 1/4 cup jello in blender with pears and cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Add remaining jello and blend.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish.
This is a real family favorite.

title: artichoke-rice salad
directions: Cook rice, omit butter and cool.
Add onions, peppers, olives and drained artichokes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Stir in soft Cheddar cheese.
Add pineapple (with all the juice drained, may have to squeeze juice from pineapple).
Add pecans, pepper, onion and salt.
Chill overnight.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together until creamy.

title: italian sauce
directions: Combine together hamburger, oil, onion and garlic and fry in skillet.
Drain grease.
Put in slow cooker along with remaining ingredients.
Cook slow all day on low heat.

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, onion, pickle, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Let sit until ready.
Five minutes before serving, add crushed potato chips and cabbage. Mix and then put more crushed potato chips on top of each serving.

title: cauliflower and carrot dish
directions: Cook cauliflower.
Cut carrots in 1/2-inch slices.
Cook until just tender.
Mix soup, milk and salt.
Pour over vegetables in a casserole dish.
Brown crumbs in butter in frypan.
Crumble cracker crumbs and butter mixture over top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grilled caribbean chicken breasts
directions: In a large, shallow bowl, mix together orange juice, orange peel, olive oil, lime juice, ginger, hot pepper sauce and oregano. Add chicken, turning to coat.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator overnight or for at least 3 hours.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and place on prepared grill about 6 inches from heat.
Grill, turning, for about 10 minutes or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.

title: best ever blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Add blueberries and stir carefully to coat.
In a
small bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk and margarine.
Add to blueberry mixture; stir just until blended.
Fill greased muffin pans (or use paper cupcake liners) 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with almonds and sugar.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes, until pick comes out clean at 400°.

title: tamale pie dip
directions: Crumble tamales in saucepan.
Add other ingredients.
Stir over medium heat until cheese melts.
Serve hot with Fritos.

title: jill's pride of iowa cookies
directions: Use a large bowl; beat eggs, then add sugars and butter.
Mix well by hand.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts and chips.
Drop large dollops on Airbake sheet. Bake for 9 to 11 minutes at 375°.

title: cheryl's candy
directions: Melt almond bark.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour melted almond bark over ingredients; mix well.
Spoon out on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: party pizzas
directions: Pour Velveeta cheese over browned sausage.
Stir in ketchup Worcestershire sauce and basil.
Spread on party rye bread, approximately 2 loaves; freeze on cookie sheets.
Stack and wrap in foil or plastic wrap.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: kelly's barbecue ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients except ribs, salt and pepper.

title: southern pecan oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Add oleo and let stand until oleo is melted.
Stir in sugar, eggs and sifted dry ingredients. Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: okinawa dango
directions: Mix all ingredients very well.	Drop
by
tablespoonful into hot oil and deep fry.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly (except bacon and tomato sauce) and pour into loaf pan.
Cover with 3 strips of bacon and tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brown rice
directions: Prepare rice according to directions, but don't add salt.
Cut bacon into 2-inch strips and cook until nearly done.
Chop onions, beans and carrots.
Add chopped vegetables to nearly done bacon and cook until tender.
Add to rice.
Add soy sauce to taste.

title: green chili pie
directions: Lightly grease 9-inch pie pan or use an 8-inch square baking pan.
Spread chilies evenly over bottom of pan.
Layer cheese evenly.
Drizzle eggs evenly over cheese.
Bake at 275° for 6 minutes.
Cut into small pieces for snacks.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute the onion, celery and green pepper in a skillet in a small amount of margarine. Add soups and tomatoes.
Debone chicken.
Add sauce and cooked spaghetti (cook spaghetti in chicken broth). Add cubed or grated Velveeta cheese. Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Salt to taste.

title: guacamole
directions: Cut avocados in half, remove pits and scoop out pulp with a spoon.
Mash pulp with a fork.
Add enough picante sauce to taste and consistency.
Season with garlic salt, pepper and a dash of Tabasco sauce.
Add lime juice.
Mix well.
Serve immediately with tortilla chips.
You can add onions, fresh jalapeno or whatever to your taste and heat tolerance.

title: chocolate snowcaps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, slowly combine flour, sugar, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, butter, peanut butter, milk, vanilla and egg until stiff dough forms.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and then roll the balls in the extra sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Immediately top each cookie with Hershey's Kiss, pressing down firmly into the edges of the cookie crack.
Remove from the cookie sheet.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Brown pork in shortening on all sides in skillet. Meanwhile drain pineapple; reserve juice. Combine brown sugar, salt and cornstarch. Stir in pineapple juice, water, vinegar and soy sauce. Remove meat from skillet. Blend cornstarch mixture into pan drippings. Add meat and cook on low heat until meat is tender. Add pineapple, green pepper and onion. Cook for 3 minutes.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Trim crust of bread and roll flat.
Mix cheese, onion, bacon and spices.
Spread small amount on each slice of bread.
Roll around asparagus spear and wrap in plastic wrap.
Freeze.

title: cantonese pork
directions: Brown
pork
in
oil
in skillet.
Drain, if necessary. Place pork in Dutch oven or crock-pot and cover with onion and pepper strips.
Combine
rest
of
ingredients and pour over. Cover and cook
on low for 6 to 8 hours in crock-pot or 3 to 4 hours on stove, adding water, if necessary.
Serve with rice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add milk; stir.
Add corn, egg yolks and oleo.
Beat egg whites until a peak forms; fold into corn mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Reserve broth.
Mix soup and 3 tablespoons of butter.
Set aside.

title: spinach cheese pie(tortiera di spinaci)
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Bake pie crust for 5 minutes. Cook spinach
just until thawed.
Drain and pat dry.
Combine spinach with
the rest of the ingredients.
Pour mixture into pie crust and bake 30 to 35 minutes, until set firm.
Serve as an appetizer or luncheon.
Can be served hot or cold.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan sticks(6 dozen)
directions: Put flour, margarine, powdered sugar and pecans in a large bowl; mix thoroughly using your hands.
Pack the mixture into a 1-pound margarine box (it will all fit into the box).
Secure with rubber band.
Chill until hard.
Peel off paper box and cut into 5 pieces, using sharp knife (width of box).
Slice each piece into slices approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12
minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all of the ingredients together. Bake in slow oven for 1 hour.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Prepare top and bottom pie crust.
Cover fruit with apple juice and add cinnamon.
Add enough cornstarch to thicken while fruit is cooking.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add Equal and stir well.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° until crust is golden.
Taste just like a "red" pie. Delicious!

title: casa fiesta world series dip
directions: In a large, shallow 9 x 13-inch pan or dish, layer ingredients in order listed.
Place tortilla chips around the edges of tray or pan.
Fast and easy dip for a gathering.

title: hot browns
directions: Heat until cheese melts.
Place toast on bottom of baking pan. Place turkey on toast.
Cover with a layer of tomatoes and a layer of bacon.
Then pour cheese sauce over all and broil until hot.

title: pork and apple stew
directions: Layer in a large pan: onion slice, pork chops, salt and pepper, brown sugar, water and apples.
Toss fat strips in brown sugar and lay on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: no bake brownies
directions: Combine milk and chocolate in pan.
Cook until chocolate melts. With electric mixer, mix in crumbs and nuts.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: luxury casserole
directions: Drain green beans and lima beans, spread in large shallow casserole dish. Mix salt, mayonnaise, soups, pimentos and onions. Pour mixture over beans and top with grated cheese. Cover cheese with crumbs (dressing mix). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: honeyed pork chops
directions: Place chops in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with sliced onion. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: noodles
directions: Put flour in a bowl (more than you need).
Make a well in the center of flour.
Add eggs and water.
Salt.
Mix the eggs and water.
Keep mixing until you have a stiff dough.
Roll out into 14 to 16-inch circles.
Dry a while, cut into noodles.
Cook in broth. Freezes well.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and put in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: individual pizzas
directions: On a greased cookie sheet spread 2 biscuits per pizza.
Form a large circle and build up sides.
You might have to grease your hands to make it easier to handle dough.
Brown hamburger; drain. Dice onion; drain mushrooms.
On each pizza place 2 tablespoons sauce; add meat, cheese and whatever topping desired.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with green chiles and feta cheese. Pound the chicken breasts as thin as you can.
Spread cream cheese mixture and roll the breasts.
Wrap bacon around the breasts and secure with a tooth pick.
Place in a 9x12 baking dish and bake in a 350 degree oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4.
After cooking these freeze very well.

title: simple cobbler
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch shallow baking dish.
Mix flour and butter together.
Blend in sugar and milk.
Pour over fruit (cut in chunks).
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes until brown and firm in 350° oven.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a Pyrex dish. Cook in oven at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: dilly balls
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, onions, egg and seasoning.
Shape into small balls.
Brown.
Stir in soup, water and pickle.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Yummy!

title: no-cook peanut butter bars
directions: Melt sugar and corn syrup. Add peanut butter and melt. Put corn flakes in large bowl and add peanut butter mixture. Mix well. Pour onto cookie sheet and flatten. Cool, cut and enjoy!

title: wine-wassail bowl
directions: Combine water, sugar and spices. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and allow to stand for 1 hour.
At the end of the hour, remove spices, if desired. Add fruit juices and wine.
Heat to serve.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add ingredients in order.
Pour in 9-inch pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn down to 300° until done.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix warm water, yeast and sugar together in large bowl.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add oil, egg and salt.
Stir well.
Slowly add flour, mixing well.
Dough will be sticky.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and store in refrigerator until ready to roll out (at least 3 hours).
It will keep about 3 days if refrigerated.
Roll out on well floured board.
Work in flour to keep from being too sticky to handle.
Cut with biscuit cutter; dip cutter in flour. Place rolls on greased cookie sheet and let rise in warm place, about 1 hour or until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen medium sized rolls.

title: easy cocktail shrimp for 40
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, juice, seasoned salt and lemon pepper.

In a 9 x 13-inch oven dish, layer cream cheese mix, cocktail sauce and cut shrimp. Top with 3/4 cup chopped green peppers, 9 chopped green onions and 1 cup small sliced black olives and grated Monterey Jack cheese. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: duet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling liquid; add sherbet, stirring until melted.
Add mandarins, pour into 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Fill center with Ambrosia Fruit Salad.

title: haitian black beans(my favorite)
directions: Drain the soaked beans and add them to the water in a medium saucepan. Bring the water to a boil.
Reduce the heat, cover the pan and simmer the beans for 30 minutes.
Add the onions, green pepper, garlic, bay leaves, salt, pepper, oregano and thyme. Simmer the ingredients 1 hour longer.
Check after 40 minutes and add more water, if necessary. Stir in the vinegar and simmer the beans for another minute.
Five minutes before serving the beans, remove the bay leaves. Stir in the pimientos and heat the beans, stirring often
to avoid scorching.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves and butter melts. Let cool slightly.

title: refrigerator nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in vanilla and egg. Sift dry ingredients together; add nuts.
Gradually add to sugar mixture, beating well after each addition.
Shape in long rolls (2-inch diameter) on waxed paper.
Chill in refrigerator several hours, overnight or even a week.
Slice 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 400° oven about 7 minutes. Yields about 6 dozen.
On hot days, slice a little thicker.
Be sure to return remaining dough to refrigerator while each batch of cookies bake.

title: mary ellen's blueberry cream jello
directions: Mix (fold) all together.
Cool until firm, then add/spread topping on it.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Bring rice to boil in 1 cup of water with 1/4 teaspoon salt. Cover and set aside.
Core cabbage and boil until leaves are soft. Trim heavy part of leaves and allow to cool.
Fry onion in oil; add meat, rice, salt and pepper.
Set aside to cool.
Add eggs to mixture and mix thoroughly.
Fill cabbage leaves with mixture; roll up and place in roaster pan, one next to the other.
Mix tomato soup with 3 cans of water.
Pour over rolled cabbage.
Cover with leftover leaves.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious!

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add Cool Whip. Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Refrigerate about 3 hours.

title: chocolate fruit cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine eggs and sugar, cut chocolate in small pieces; add nuts and fruit and chocolate to flour mixture.

title: judy's baked chicken
directions: Mix soups, onion mix and water together.
Pour over chicken which has been arranged in oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a frying pan, cook onions, celery and green peppers in oil until tender.
In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, add these to remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, for several hours until desired thickness is reached.
Stir occasionally.
Cook, uncovered, for last of period of time to hasten thickening.

title: beef or venison jerky
directions: Cut meat in strips 3/8 to 1/4-inch cut against the grain for more tender and with the grain for chewy jerky.
The meat will cut best when semi-frozen.
The thinner the slice; the faster the drying time.
Marinate for at least 2 hours.
Drain with colander, and then place on trays to dry.
Do not overlap strips and turn over at least once during drying process.
Dry at 145 degrees for 6 to 10 hours.
Its ready when it bends likes a green willow without breaking.
Store in airtight container.
Refrigerate for long periods of time.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put eggs in double boiler.
Add vinegar and sugar, beating constantly until thick and smooth.
Remove from burner.
Add butter and cool.
When cool, fold in whipped cream and fruit. Turn into mold and put in refrigerator.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cut the top half of muffin cups so they are shallower.
Melt the chocolate chips in microwave in glass bowl at 50% power for 2 minutes or until melted.
Using a teaspoon, spoon a portion of chocolate in the middle of the muffin cup, drawing it up the edges.
Repeat with remaining muffin cups.
Put in fridge so chocolate hardens.
Combine peanut butter, powdered sugar and salt in a medium bowl and put in microwave for 1 minute.
Spoon a portion of peanut butter into each of the chocolate-coated cups. Put back in fridge to harden, Re-Melt the rest of the chocolate and spread a layer on top of the peanut butter.
Return to fridge to harden.
Makes 12 peanut butter cups.

title: impossible garden pie
directions: Sprinkle into a 10-inch pie pan (oiled) the zucchini, tomatoes, onions and cheese.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper. Pour over vegetables in pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fletcher's fruit salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Put in a large pan.
Gently pour tomato juice over the meat loaf and into the pan.
Top with ketchup.
Cook at 350° in oven for 1 hour or 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate a couple hours until ready to serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With electric mixer (not a food processor), whip all ingredients except walnuts and nutmeg until light.
Stir in walnuts and put into a buttered casserole.
Spread evenly and grate fresh nutmeg over the top.
Bake 45 minutes until golden.

title: broccoli baked potato
directions: Boil potatoes until a fork can be inserted easily.
Once potatoes are cooked, split them down the middle.
Place the potatoes in a baking pan.
While potatoes are cooking, saute broccoli.
Once broccoli is finished cooking, spoon broccoli onto the split potatoes.
Top with Cheez Whiz.
Preheat oven at 325°. Place pan in oven.
Let cook approximately 15 to 20 minutes. Before serving sprinkle bacon bits over the top.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Combine yeast, brown sugar, peanuts and salt; add 1 1/2 cups flour to this.
Set aside.
Heat peanut butter and water to 120° to 130°.
Add to mixture and stir until mixed, then add 3 cups flour and stir/mix 2 minutes.
Place into lightly greased bowl and allow to rise for 1 hour.
With spoon, stir down batter and continue to stir for 30 seconds.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Let rise, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix together flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to first mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Sprinkle brown sugar, nuts and nutmeg on top.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: quick donuts
directions: Separate biscuits.
Cut out small hole in center with cutter. Drop donut and hole in deep fryer.
Cook evenly.
Remove and dip in powdered sugar.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place cut up chicken into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cranberry sauce, onion soup mix and French dressing; mix well. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tender. Serve with rice and vegetables.

title: tortilla stew
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt, pepper and chili powder. Add water, tomatoes, beans, chilies and corn.
Simmer 1 hour. About 5 minutes before serving, add tortilla pieces and simmer until hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: onion crusted chicken
directions: Place each piece of chicken between two sheets of wax paper and flatten to 1/4-inch using meat mallet or rolling pin. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine butter, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Stir well.
Dredge chicken in butter mixture, then in crushed onion rings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in shallow glass baking dish at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes.
If desired, additional 1/2 cup grated cheese may be sprinkled over top of casserole before baking.

title: crock pot pizza
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped onion and green pepper.
Add sauces.
Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Layer, starting with meat, noodles, pepperoni, cheeses and mushrooms.
Or whatever you like.
You should have approximately three layers.
Simmer in small deep crock pot for 4 hours.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl and add sugar, cinnamon, banana, pineapple, oil, eggs and pecan.
Stir well.
Do not use mixer.
Bake in Bundt pan for about 65 minutes at 350°.
Be sure to grease and flour pan.

title: chicken biscuit stew
directions: Make sauce:
Melt butter.
Mix in flour and spices.
Add broth and milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Simmer until bubbly.
Arrange biscuits over hot chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter and banana sandwich
directions: Spread evenly the mayo on 1 slice of bread.
Spread the peanut butter on other slice.
Cut banana in small slices and place on bread.
Place the 2 slices together and commence to eat.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute garlic and onion.
Add rice; stir until translucent. Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fabulous party dip
directions: Cut a hole in top of bread loaf, about 5-inches in diameter. Remove soft bread from cut portion and discard.
Reserve crust to make top for loaf.
Scoop out most of soft inside portion of the loaf and save for stuffing or bread crumbs.

title: grapefruit cup
directions: Cut grapefruit in half, remove segments and cut away all fibers.
Retain juice.
Arrange segments in the empty shells. Pour juice in a pan with red hots and honey; bring just to a boil. Pour over grapefruit.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage and biscuit bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In frying pan, brown sausage and drain. Add onion, green pepper, celery, mixed vegetables and soup; mix well.
Heat until hot.
Pour into 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Separate biscuits.
Arrange on hot meat.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until biscuits are brown.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: picadillo
directions: Heat olive oil and add finely chopped onions, garlic and green pepper.
Add ground beef, stirring every few minutes until brown; drain.
Add other ingredients and allow to simmer over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.
Can also be served over rice.

title: bean soup
directions: Combine all of ingredients and simmer until onion is tender, about 30 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift 3 1/2 cups flour and soda together.
Add buttermilk; mix together.
Add dates, nuts and orange slices.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry delight
directions: First Layer:
Crumble angel food cake in 8 x 10-inch container.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Wash required amount of rice under cold water in strainer. Soak overnight in cold water.
Drain and stir into 3 times the amount of boiling water (1 cup rice requires 3 cups water). Parboil for 5 minutes only.
Remove from heat; let soak in the same water (covered) for 1 hour.
Drain, wash in cold water and cook as directed in recipe.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Add seasonings, corn and sauce.
Line bottom of a 2 1/2-quart flat bottomed casserole dish with 1/2 of cornmeal mush.
Add meat mixture and put rest of cornmeal mush on top.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, Worcestershire sauce, cream and onion mix. Form into meatballs.
Broil 10 minutes or until done.

title: chili
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and bell pepper (optional).
Add remaining ingredients and simmer gently 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Heat the jello and crushed pineapple until jello is melted. Let set until jello is in soft stage.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let set until jello is firm.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil sugar, salt, pepper, water, vinegar and oil.
Let cool. Drain beans, corn and peas.
Pour over them the cooled mixture. Add onion, peppers and carrot.
Refrigerate overnight.
If large cans of vegetables are used, increase sauce by 1/4 cup.

title: scrambled eggs(for four)
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; beat slightly.
Pour egg mixture into heated pan cooked to desired doneness, stirring frequently.
Serve at once.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Bake 3 hours at 350°.
Shred up and return to oven.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine, mixing until well blended. Add chili sauce and horseradish to cream cheese mixture, mixing until well blended.
Add shrimp and mix well.
Chill.

title: old-fashioned meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into a loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar.
Mix well until creamy.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each one.
Add 1/2 flour, beat well.
Add vanilla, mix well.
Pour into cake pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Break egg into cup and stir. Fill cup with milk to make 1 cup of milk and egg mixture. Makes 3 double crust pie shells. May need to add additional flour. This still won't fail.

title: cindy's chicken and green beans
directions: Steam green beans 5 minutes.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Place half the beans in pan.
Cover with half of the onion and garlic.
Place other half of beans on top and cover with rest of onions and garlic.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour wine and tomatoes on top of beans.
Sprinkle half the herbs on top. Wash and dry chicken.
Place skin side up on top of beans.
Spray chicken with Pam.
Sprinkle with chicken spice and the rest of the herbs.
Bake uncovered at 375° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until chicken is cooked.

title: fried rice with chicken
directions: Combine chicken, soy sauce and salt; let stand 15 minutes. In large skillet, melt Crisco.
Add rice and cook over medium heat until rice is golden brown, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; add chicken mixture, bouillon granules and hot water.
Cover; cook 20 to 25 minutes, until rice is tender.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until liquid is absorbed.
Push rice mixture to side; add eggs.
Cook until almost set; stir into rice.
Stir in lettuce.
Serve at once with additional soy sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: golden donuts
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and 1/3 milk.
Sift and add 3 cups flour and other dry ingredients.
Add melted lard and vanilla; add enough flour to make dough stiff enough to handle. Roll about 1/3-inch thick and cut with donut cutter.
Fry in deep hot fat.
Dredge with powdered sugar.

title: corn pudding
directions: Place corn, eggs, flour and sugar into blender.
Turn off and on 2 times at low speed.
Add milk and stir until blended.
Butter baking dish and cut up rest of butter into dish.
Pour mixture in center of dish and bake at 325°.
Stir twice during first 15 minutes and continue baking another 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix together all other ingredients in large bowl.
Blend well; add yeast (store in refrigerator in airtight bowl).
Will keep about 1 week.
Chill and drop by spoonful into greased muffin tins or on greased cookie sheet. Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna and place in bowl.
Chop vegetables as small as you can.
Chop gherkins a little bigger; add all to tuna and mix well. Add salt and pepper and juice.
Mix.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Put in refrigerator 2 hours.
Mix and serve.

title: quesadillas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup of the cheese evenly over half of each tortilla.
Top cheese with remaining ingredients.
Fold tortilla over filling.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake about 5 minutes or just until cheese is melted.
Serve quesadillas whole or cut each into 3 wedges, beginning cuts from center of folded sides.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt peanut butter chips, 1 cup condensed milk and 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir occasionally. Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts.
Spread mixture into a wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.
In small pan, melt semi-sweet chocolate chips, remaining condensed milk and butter.
Spread chocolate mixture on top of peanut butter mixture.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge into cutting board.
Peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Mixture will be crumbly. Mix with your hands.
Press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Blend softened cream cheese and sugar.
Add 3 eggs and rest of dry cake mix, sifted.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
At low speed, slowly add milk and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Pour into crust and bake at 300° for 60 minutes.
Cool, cover and refrigerate. Cover with Cool Whip.

title: beef sherry
directions: Cut beef (I use stew beef) into bite sized pieces.
Do NOT braise.
Combine the beef with soups and sherry.
Pour into buttered casserole and cover. Bake at 300 degrees for 3 hours. Clean slice, and saute mushrooms in butter.
Add to casserole about 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: wine cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, sift together cake mix, pudding mix and nutmeg.
In another bowl, beat eggs thoroughly; add oil, wine and water.
Slowly add egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter bundt cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Blend in peanut butter, then flour.
Pour into lightly greased 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Spoon into baking dish. Combine 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup of melted margarine.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon koolers
directions: Mix together and pat ingredients into baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: 12 layer jello salad
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to cherry Jell-O.
Take out 1/2 cup and add to 1/3 cup sour cream.
Pour into 12 x 8-inch dish (2 quarts).
Chill 20 minutes or until set.
Add 3 tablespoons cold water to remaining Jell-O and pour on top of first layer.
Chill 20 minutes or until set.
Repeat with each remaining box of Jell-O.

title: fiesta tamale pie
directions: Heave oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef, onion and garlic until meat is brown and onion is tender. Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, corn, olives and seasonings; heat to boiling.
Pour into an ungreased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix cornmeal, milk and eggs and spoon onto meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cucumber-dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve with Bugles.
Makes 4 1/2 cups dip.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; boil for 7 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow; mix. Quickly add nuts and flour.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Let cool before cutting.
Makes 4 pounds.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Scramble hamburg.
Cook rice as directed.
Mix hamburg and cans of zucchini.
Add 3/4 package of cheese and cooked rice.
Mix well.
Put all ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake covered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Mix eggs, milk and baking powder.
Soak chicken in mixture. Roll in flour and salt; let set up.
Deep fry in peanut oil until golden brown.
Sprinkle cashews over chicken.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad(serves 12)
directions: Shred lettuce in bottom of large flat serving dish or bowl. Sprinkle onion, celery and water chestnuts over lettuce in layers. Break peas apart, still
frozen, over the water chestnuts. Spread mayonnaise, like frosting, over top.
Sprinkle sugar and grated cheese to completely cover the top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top with bacon crumbles.
Do not toss; each serving should go to bottom of bowl and get some of each layer.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Stir together condensed milk,
peanut butter, and vanilla. Add biscuit mix, stir well.
Shape into one inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on baking sheet.
With thumb, make an indention in center of each ball.
Bake in 375° oven 8 to
10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove
from oven and place a chocolate kiss in center of each cookie.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: no bake candy bar pie
directions: Put candy bars in double boiler with 2 tablespoons hot water until melted.
Cool 30 minutes. Fold in whipped topping and vanilla.
Put in graham cracker crust.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, turmeric and celery seed and bring to hard boil. Pour over cucumbers, onions, and banana peppers. Let cool, 1 hour, cover and store.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Grease and
flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Set aside. In a medium
bowl,
combine
strawberries,
oil and eggs. Set aside. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, soda and nuts.
Add the strawberry mixture to dry ingredients; mix just until blended.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate dessert cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt three times.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add melted chocolate and walnuts.
Add flour and buttermilk, folding in lightly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased angel food pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini until just tender-crisp; drain and mix with margarine.
In separate bowl, mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese; save 1/4 cup for topping.
Mix together with zucchini. Layer with Mozzarella cheese.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Remove heart from cabbage.
Cover with boiling water; let stand until cabbage is wilted.
Separate leaves, being careful not to break.
Drain; dry on paper toweling.
Melt butter in a heavy skillet; saute pepper, onion and celery 2 minutes.
Add cooked rice and sausage to vegetables.
Mix well; season.
Put about 1/4 cup mixture on each cabbage leaf.
Roll with filling inside; fasten edges with toothpicks.
Place in a greased baking dish. Add tomato juice, water and whole onion.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Melt approximately 30 vanilla caramels over a double boiler or use one jar of caramel sundae topping.
Pour over apples and place mixture in an unbaked 4-inch shell.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture is crumbly. Add almonds or walnuts if desired and sprinkle mixture over pie. Bake at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: raisin apple streudel
directions: Cook the raisins, water, salt, sugar, lemon juice and cornstarch together in a saucepan until thickened.
Add butter; cool.
Roll in pie crust (as a jelly roll).
Bake in a 450° oven until golden brown.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook beef, onion and pepper until tender and brown.
Season to taste.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: foil-grilled peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of green peppers.
Remove all seeds and membranes.
Wash inside and outside.
Mix chili beans, corn and catsup; lightly stuff each pepper.
Wrap each pepper securely in double thickness, heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Cook on medium coals 15 to 20 minutes or grill 3 to 4 inches from hot coals 30 to 40 minutes, turning once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except marshmallows.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake 5 minutes.
